{"product_id": "201870", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "A game I played frequently on the XBOX 360. AC Revelations is one of the best Assassins Creed (if not adventure) games of all time. The conclusion to the Ezio trilogy had one of the saddest, yet most epic endings I've ever seen in a video game.\n9/10", "hours": 10.1, "username": "IslandKing", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "When I read reviews prior to playing this, a good amount of them said that this game got right what Brotherhood got wrong. It actually just gets them more wrong. I play games to have fun, not to be told how much of a failure I am.\nYou play as a senile old fart who miraculously pulls off a lot of things that even Desmond/the Animus has difficulty recreating, not great for gameplay when the directional controls are just as dodgy as the last game.\nI did get this game for its story and how that ties back into the central plot, but I can't say there's much else that makes this game worthwhile.", "hours": 23.7, "username": "<Kl0n[d1k]E>", "products": 510, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 5, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "Actually awesome. I loved the first two and couldn't stand brotherhood but this is a great game. Gameplay improved over brotherhood, improved graphics, awesome story and finally some answers. Loved it!", "hours": 66.2, "user_id": "76561198039194257", "username": "nymaway", "products": 28, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
