{"product_id": "201870", "page": 8, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-25", "text": "This chapter of Assassin's Creed is one of the best I have played. Soundtrack was brilliantly composed by the legendary Jesper Kyd, with collaboration of Lorne Balfe. Instruments was used perfectly to fit in with Turkish atmosphere. Especially 'Galata Tower'. I absolutely like the storyline and curious to find out more on what's going on next. However I just don't like how repetitive Assassin's Creed is. As in copy paste gameplay mechanics like destroy towers just like in previous chapter - Assassin's Creed Brotherhood.", "hours": 20.3, "username": "ReconSixth", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
