{"product_id": "201870", "page": 10, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-22", "text": "This is, storywise, my personal favorite, so far, in the Assassin's Creed franchise. Since I played this after playing the previous ones, I managed a connection with Ezio's character that made me tear up at the end. Specially with the short movie, Embers.\nThe playability is really good, with very little bugs, which I can't claim for the following titles. I'm currently suffering, err, playing Assassin's Creed Rogue and boy oh boy I want to smash my keyboard...\nLoved the mechanics. I find myself missing the parachute on later games...\nAnyway, love this game, love the city, love the language.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "maxniko", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
