{"product_id": "201870", "page": 15, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-10", "text": "Won't work in my PC with a Nvidia GTX980. Graphic stuttering makes the game unplayable. I'd steer away from this game if you have the same card. I wish I know before I got it. Shame, as I have many other Assasin's Creed games and other Ubisoft games. I just don't have the patience anymore to rip apart my graphics card, settings, drivers and use other tools to get an old game to work properly.\nThis game goes in the trash.", "hours": 1.1, "user_id": "76561197970361517", "username": "x[grendel]", "products": 180, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 15, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-09", "text": "Revelations feels like a completely different Assassin's Creed game, mostly because of it's atmosphere and the country it takes place in. At first it was a downside for me, but I started to like the change over time, although I still think that Brotherhood was better. I would recommend the game to people that really like the series, as it continues the story of Ezio, who also meets Altair from the first game and Desmond.\nOverall it is a good game, but it has three main flaws: If you run it on Windows 10 it is very glitchy and unplayable, but fortunately it's easy to fix as you only have to remove one file. Secondly the face of the main character was completely changed, what I will never understand and I think it's unnecessary. Thirdly, I wish it was longer, as it is the shortest AC game.", "hours": 22.6, "username": "PurpleCheshire", "products": 108, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 15, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-09", "text": "Very beautiful ending to Ezio's remarkable story! The Ezio Trilogy is definitely the best part of the Assassin's Creed series, and these games will always hold a special place in my heart. Some of the newer ones truly lack the magic of the beautiful soundtracks and great locations that the Ezio Trilogy had so fondly contained.\nRevelations is the most relaxing Assassin's Creed adventure, in my opinion. Masyaf and Constantinople are both beautifully created, and recreated, in this game. The soundtrack is beautiful as always, and the gameplay is refined to feel and play as well as it did before, if not better. However, during the battle, I found that the bombs are absolutely useless. I never used them, did you?\nIn conclusion, I can only add that I'm  playing this game not in the first time, but I have many positive emotions. It makes happy))", "hours": 8.4, "user_id": "76561198168337373", "username": "Hroft", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
