{"product_id": "201870", "page": 25, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-19", "text": "The gameplay is relatively short(not counting time spend on collectibles), however the missions are fun and breathtaking, they are the best mission design comparing to it's previous work. The story give me goose bumps, linking Ezio, Altair and Desmond, once again displays the grand world of AC series. On the contrary, the DLCs are bland and boring, with useless multiplayer items and depressing game mode in Lost of Archive\nUbisoft is one of the most innovative game developer I've ever seen, keep adding new entertaining elements in their new work, in this particular one they added bomb system, tower defense and new kind of hidden blade\nJust a fine piece of work, I'm eager to play the rest of the series", "hours": 24.3, "user_id": "76561198337503770", "username": "MiX7", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 25, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-15", "text": "This one surprised me. I didn't expect it to become my favourite thus far in the series. I really enjoyed playing old Ezio. Great story and reflection on the Ezio trilogy. If I had to name one thing I like the most in the AC: Revelations I couldn't decide between the beautiful city of Istanbul or the hookblade.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "Zeus_CM", "products": 432, "early_access": false}
