{"product_id": "201870", "page": 28, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-20", "text": "I've been pretty harsh on the Assassin's Creed games before 3 including Brotherhood but this game really is amazing so far. I've not beaten it quite yet at the time of this posting but I thought I've played enough to give it a thumbs up. The issue with the controls that AC 2 engine games suffer from isn't nearly that noticable and you can start to do some cool attack moves. Sure, it's no where near 3's level but it's a huge step towards it. The character is more interesting than he was in Brotherhood and I think the storyline is better too. Props to them for this game, I recommend it.", "hours": 20.1, "user_id": "76561198022039830", "username": "Monroe", "products": 515, "early_access": false}
