{"product_id": "201870", "page": 32, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "I would have to say that this was the last good assassins creed game and the last assassins creed that actually meant assassins creed before the series started to get boring. I mean ac 3 was ok but I still preferred the original ac games because the new once are just compleat garbage I mean there ok but they don't really have a story all you have to do is kill the target and that's it I mean you get a back story of the character, but the new games just feel boring and plan. So ya revelations was the last good ac game rakuezka de patche ezio", "hours": 14.3, "user_id": "76561198165206780", "username": "DarkElm", "products": 126, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 32, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-01-19", "text": "For those who like repetitive and/or similar game play like those in AC Brotherhood, this is your kind of game.\nFor those who are expecting similar yet provide an entirely unique and new game play (a.k.a me) this is not for you.\nTo be fair, there are new things such as the variety of the bombs.\nOther than that, to me at least, the rest are pretty much the same.\nHowever, the story line is still good, so that what kept me playing.", "hours": 26.7, "username": "Fara", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
