{"product_id": "201870", "page": 36, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-12", "text": "I've attained 100% game completion.\nPros:\n- Great gameplay.\n- Great graphics.\n- Good story.\n- Fun and enjoyable city exploration, and plenty to do for completionists like myself.\n- Fantastic way to conclude Ezio's trilogy and life as an Assassin.\nCons:\n- There were a few glitches here and there, such as when you have to fight a man called Shakulu later in the game, the game crahses and stops responding. Those who experience this issue should go into task manager, right click on the process \"ACR.exe\" and click \"set affinity\". From there, disable all threads except for one. \"Core 0\" should remain ticked, if it's literally unplayably laggy, then sometimes enabling \"Core 1\" as well as \"Core 0\" works, or at least it did with my 8700K . This will make the game lag heaps, but after the fight has finished you can turn them back on. You don't need to restart in between re-enabling. The same fix works for the third Altair mission.\n- Again, much like ACB the game is reletively short at only 9 sequences, but after all, it is just an expansion of AC2.\nRating: 9.5/10.", "hours": 83.0, "username": "DSprite", "products": 110, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 36, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-11", "text": "An improvement over the previous titles in game mechanics, Assassin's creed Revelations gives the player a satisfiying ending to the stories of it's first two protagonists, Ezio Auditore and Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad. While the plot is a tad weaker than the other entries in the Desmod Story Arc, it's characters are rich and vibrant and the conclusion makes up for any misgivings you might have. All in all, Revelations is a visually beautiful game with a soundtrack to match. In the end you'll wish you could go back and experience it for the first time all over again.\n10/10 would assassinate again.", "hours": 3.0, "user_id": "76561198151309277", "username": "theseasdancingotter", "products": 88, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 36, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-06", "text": "I bought it just to show my respect to Ezio Auditore.", "hours": 46.5, "user_id": "76561198059343366", "username": "Wolverine", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 36, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-06", "text": "When I was a young man,\nI had liberty, but I did not see it.\nI had time, but I did not know it.\nI had love, but I did not feel it.\nMany decades would pass before I understood the meaning of all three.\nAnd now, the twilight of my life, this understand has passed into contentment.\nLove, liberty and time, once so disaposable, are the fuels that drive me forward.\nAnd love, most especially, for you, our children, our brothers and sisters,\nand for the vast and wonderful world that give us life.\nEndless affections, Mia Sofia.\n\u2014\u2014Ezio Auditore", "hours": 24.2, "username": "Jace Herondale", "products": 114, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
