{"product_id": "201870", "page": 42, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-28", "text": "After purchasing this game, and downloading ubisoft's launcher, I have been told repeatedly that I don't own it. Every few days Ubisoft blocks out my cd key and their customer support is abysmal at helping me get verification back. I'll not buy another title from them again.", "hours": 14.2, "user_id": "76561198273459376", "username": "c7bamford", "products": 56, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 42, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-26", "text": "Revelations is not as good as AC 2 or Brotherhood but I still love this game mainly because of how well it closes Ezio and Altair\u2019s story. This game has a lot of great moments, some of the best in the whole franchise. These very well done character moments with both Ezio and Altair as well as great action set pieces such as the first hour of the game or the tombs of the Masyaf keys make this game very memorable.  A lot of the story missions and side plots feel like filler and it is not very interesting which brings this game back a lot as well as the additions that the series didn\u2019t need like the tower defense and bomb crafting. Even though Constantinople is a great setting for this game it\u2019s not as interesting or memorable as the previous games settings. These problems stop this game from being amazing but I still consider it to be a great game and it closes off the Ezio trilogy perfectly.\n8/10 (Great)", "hours": 16.4, "username": "David0vi\u0107", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
