{"product_id": "201870", "page": 47, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-16", "text": "Great game, although not the best in the series but definitely worth it. Loved the hook blade\nEzio Auditore will be missed.. :|", "hours": 0.2, "username": "`Hannibal.Lecter", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 47, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-15", "text": "Can't say I really cared for this game, you could not pay me any less than $1,000 to play it again(I am a college student, so my dignity is lower than usual). I was dragging my feet through the entire game, but I spent money on it so I made myself finish it. Don't bother with this one, but you should read up on the story line online. It does have a somewhat interesting story line, but the game is not worth the time and money.\nThe one thing I did like that this game added was the hook, so you can jump farther and hook onto ziplines.", "hours": 14.1, "username": "heartofscylla", "products": 37, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 47, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-13", "text": "The game is very nice, it had a couple of crashes and stutters on my pc, nut the story is great.", "hours": 29.2, "user_id": "76561198145334469", "username": "Subzerovixen", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 47, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-12", "text": "This game is a must have if you have played the last two, also if you want to continue onto AC3. But it isn't that good of a game, so don't put you're expectations high. Or average, for that matter. Instead of continuing the awesomeness of Renaissance Italy, and adventuring, killing guards, retrieving medieval artifacts... Nope! Ezio's last expedition as an Assassin takes place in... Constanople? WHY? Lame additions to this game include some hook thing that lets you jump an extra 2 inches away, and making bombs. In this game you also get a dumb den defense metagame that makes you feel like you're playing a $1.99 mobile game from the app store instead of an AC game. Basically, Ezio learns how to make bombs in the middle east, and learns how to magically place troops in front of some wooden spikes to defend a building. This game was painful to play. If Ubi wanted to make a cool game with Ottomans and Saracens, by all means they should've, but with Ezio? This game is undeserving of Ezio. This game feels like it should be a $6 DLC for the first Assassin's Creed game. By far the best part of this game is the cutscenes, and I don't mean this jokingly. This game reveals so much... hence \"revelations\", literally revealing the missing scenarios of Altair's life, including his death (not a spoiler, come on. we knew it was coming). We also see Ezio retire in this game. Sorry. But at least it's a happy ending, which I'll let you discover.", "hours": 22.0, "username": "\u2720 The Italian Spaniard \u269c", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 47, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-12", "text": "epic game and is the only but best assassins creed game i own but is amazing and fun all at once it is just the glitches in videos that are disterbing so overall its a really good game", "hours": 32.5, "username": "Kojiro Nishi", "products": 20, "early_access": false}
