{"product_id": "201870", "page": 48, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-07-16", "text": "I'ved always loved the Assasins creed series (yes even 1), but Revelations was just...meh. The bomb mechanic was annoying to use and the story started to go downhill. I've always played Assasins creed to as close to 100% as I possibly could but I can't even finish the story for this game. How disapointing. Sure the assasination mechanics are still mostly there, but stop at Brotherhood if you can unless you just want this for the additional gameplay.", "hours": 6.3, "username": "Beat_Elite", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 48, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-16", "text": "The story's shorter than the previous 2 games and 30 mins of unskippable credits.\nNice conclusion to Ezio's storyline.", "hours": 11.7, "username": "Binary Bandit", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
