{"product_id": "201870", "page": 49, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-15", "text": "This game is not as good as Assassins Creed Brotherhood or AC3 but it still provides a fun gameplay. The hook blade is handy in scaling walls, but you'll end up (at least I did) using your wrist pistol more often than the previous games, as you face tougher enemies like Janissaries that carry two weapons most times instead of Halberd wielding guys in clunky armor. Ezio is an old fart but still runs around and jumps across buildings as if he never aged a day. Age has no meaning in video games neither does time. I'd still recommend getting it, but don't expect the same type of game as Brotherhood.\n7.5/10", "hours": 31.7, "username": "Take A Bow", "products": 248, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 49, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-15", "text": "1. Multiplayer : Good.  Especially Maps.  7/10\n2. Singleplayer :\n-  Boring Den Defense : I hate it! Boring and Disgusting defense System!  To avoid it, I lowered my notorious level by bribing a herald, assassinate vizier, take off the poster.\n- Side Mission : Not good. Worse than Assassin's creed:Brotherhood. A few side missions and Mostly about Master Assassin Mission.\n- Background and Graphic, Packour and Battle : Good.\n- Secret Locations : Nice Secret Locations.", "hours": 42.4, "username": "ImperatorCaesar", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 49, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-07-14", "text": "It is the best Ezio game from a character development point of view, and the gameplay is a pot pourri of the best elements from AC2 and Brotherhood.\nYet, the gameplay didn't evolve, and its basically still the same game you're playing, reskinned.\nAnd that makes a game boring, whatever its narrative qualities may be.", "hours": 14.6, "user_id": "76561198025400075", "username": "Siegfriedfr", "products": 50, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
