{"product_id": "201870", "page": 52, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-19", "text": "Like Assassin's Creed 2 (and Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood) this game is loads of fun and has kind of a nice story. The RPG Aspects of the game are great, plus the (assassin's) guild leveling system and the constant income / town rebuilding system motivates a lot.\nAdditional features include a tower defense game for districts (fun the first time, strange anytime else, though), loads of secrets to be found and actual, real historical backgrouds for (fictional and real) persons and places.\nAnd, mind you, the Hidden Blade. And Bombs. And Parachutes. And Poison. And Trowing Knives. And Swords. And Guns. And Crossbows. And... Well, you get the idea: If it kills people, it's in this game ;-)", "hours": 33.4, "username": "High-Q-Ling", "products": 583, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 52, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-06-17", "text": "Tried coming back to finish the side quests in this game only to find out my CD key was taken. 10/10. Would buy my game and then have ubisoft tell me I dont own it again.", "hours": 23.1, "user_id": "76561197991834906", "username": "feedthemanmuffinz", "products": 269, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 52, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-16", "text": "Assassin's Creed Revelations taught me more about medieval arabian political history than I ever thought I would know. Now my family think I'm really smart. But I'm not really smart. I own all the Assassin's Creed games. How smart could I actually be?", "hours": 76.6, "username": "NRGKO", "products": 310, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 53, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-13", "text": "Mixed feelings here. This title brings some of the problems of its predecessors, like camera issues. Many times the camera turns to angles that causes more trouble than solutions. This makes the game boring.\nBesides that, this is the least challenging AC until it. Things only go wrong when flaws happen (like npcs making wrong moves or getting stuck and game controls or camera angles changing at wrong times).\nHowever, they did very nice in the game new content, like the \"tower defense\" mini game.\nBut not everything that was added is meaningful. Like the bombs. Even though they may be cool, I simply did not find proper use for them in the game (used only when the game obliged me). At the same time, the chests (already strange in the past game) got even more odd. Well, why there are chests around the city and no one cares?. I know, every game has this kind of things, but it just seemed to me too out of context.\nIn the end, the history is nice, and it fills an important gap in the series. I liked the lore and I think they did well in adding more facts and topics in the extra anymus mode.\n7/10", "hours": 10.2, "username": "Scarecrown", "products": 564, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 53, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-12", "text": "awesome <3", "hours": 35.5, "username": "Neem | Pudina \u2122", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 53, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-11", "text": "The second best AC and what a great finale' to the Ezio Aldatore trilogy.\nEzio Aldatore was the best Assassin in my opinion.", "hours": 72.0, "user_id": "76561197983468005", "username": "GamerWolfOps", "products": 671, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 53, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-11", "text": "This was the first assassins creed game I have ever played. (the first one on pc being ac brotherhood). I originally played this on the Xbox 360 then some time passed and i got into pc gaming and when i bought this and played it through to the end. I wasn't disapointed. I even teared up a little bit because i was so emotionally invested into the characters. That may be because this was my first game that i actually loved... the single player was byodiful, graphics were very nice and i could even run it at about 60 fps on my \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 computer which was suprising. The multiplayer was tough to get a grip on but i got the hang of it eventually.", "hours": 101.8, "username": "poon toons", "products": 109, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 53, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-10", "text": "Loved It Worth Playing 10 Times Over.", "hours": 48.4, "user_id": "76561198115177425", "username": "Esovanil", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
