{"product_id": "201870", "page": 60, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "Overall i think the game was a great improvement from its predecessor (Brotherhood). One of the features that i like about this game is how you are able to travel to places much quicker than before, due to the fact that you can glide over rooftops, fast travel, etc.\nThe graphic details improved a lot as well, where the textures and models are more detailed than before. Like all games, this should always happen where every year the game improves in graphic quality and this game fulfilled it.\nThe new features of weapons/items makes it more easier to play. One of these items would be a grenade that you throw to wipe out a crowd of enemies. There are more features, that you should find that out yourself. The story line is also as good as older Assassins Creed series, bring rich and full fulling experience. This is a game that should be played, but if you haven't played any Assassins Creed, i suggest you to start from AC2.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "Negan", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 60, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "The game itself feels great, the main story is really atmospheric and big, but Istanbul didn't feel as well mine as Rome was.\nIn this case the Assassins are controlling the city and the templars have to fight for it... to do that you have the known \"leader killing and tower climbing\" stuff for attacking and for defending you do some towerdefense stuff.\nFor me, I didn't really bother with the whole city stuff, I just recruited some assassins and went on with it.\nThe story went on way more dramatic than I expected, I can only recommend it.\nCompletion time about 12 hours.", "hours": 10.9, "username": "Astore", "products": 664, "early_access": false}
