{"product_id": "201870", "page": 69, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-10", "text": "+Good story and graphics\n+You can craft bombs now\n+A new blade called hookblade,it's awesome\n+You can unlock towers after a few missions,no need to wait more time like in Assassin's Creed Brotherhood\n+You are now a MENTOR and you have missions with your assassin's\n+Now you can see how % you control a\nAssasssin's Creed Brotherhood you could not see this\n+Viewpoint and you have fast travel,finnaly you don't need to buy for them\n+You can kill enemies from a zipline,so awesome\n-No automatic viewpoint when you destroy a tower like in Assassin's Creed Brotherhood\n-Press \"ESC\" for skip cinematics\n-No skip for credits", "hours": 35.5, "username": "DragonulRed", "products": 1493, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 69, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-08", "text": "Few changes from Assasins Creed II and Brotherhood gameplaywise they are still pretty much the same game.\nLiked it overall, enjoyable to play.\nEnding for the Ezio story.", "hours": 21.9, "username": "IssacFunny", "products": 209, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 69, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-08", "text": "This game is adequate.\nThe Good\nIn this game you will use time traveling Prussian warhammers and fake\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665Aladdin shamshirs to slay peasants in groups of three. Or at least thats what I did with about 92 hours of my 99 hours of gameplay. (I do not regret it) The other portions of the game that worked were the heroic sendoffs for Altair and Ezio. These characters represent the golden age of the assassins creed universe so it was nice to see them get a respectful sendoff rather then be overused in future cash cow moo creed titles\nThe Bad\nThe pacing wasn't perfect. The historical research wasn't as meticulous as in previous games. The \"Den Defense\" minigame is essentially optional... The antagonists weren\u2019t particularly threatening. Horrific Islamic war criminals are presented in a positive light and freedom fighting Greeks seeking to reclaim their homeland are presented as the villains.... (what a brave stance for the developers to take) The tutorial mission and the ending mission are basically the same. You cant steal/use Turkish rifles, you can steal from peasents in front of guards ext. The game feels repetitive and short and like the content cut from previous titles were thrown into this game as a haphazard mix.\nThe Ugly\nYou can play as Desmond as he navigates some cheap\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\"jump over things\" minigame where he monologues about his past. You may choose to simulate this experience by slapping yourself with a mouse pad.... you know where.\nBottom Line.\nThe games budget was triple slashed when it became apparent that it would only be competing for market share with Assassins Creed 3. You can see the scope that was intended for the game and literally feel missing content as you faff about. It\u2019s clear that the developers aspired only to adequacy and met it not with leaps and bounds but as a half asphyxiated carcass crawling over the finish line before collapsing but whether it\u2019s by an inch or a mile the game made it. It IS adequate, its pros do outweigh its flaws. So yeah, I liked it, I liked my time traveling Prussian warhammer and my fake\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665Aladdin sword and \"macing\" peasants was thoroughly amusing. I'd do it again. That said my hope is that they merge ASII, Brotherhood and Revelations into one super title for continuous gameplay enjoyment.\nProbably the last real Assassins Creed game.", "hours": 99.4, "user_id": "76561197993485991", "username": "Henchmen no. 25", "products": 139, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 69, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-08", "text": "Great so far! The story is a little weird but always intriguing with this series!", "hours": 14.1, "user_id": "76561198260673418", "username": "Savant_PCs", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 69, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-07", "text": "At first, I liked this game; the new game mechanics were cool, the return of Subject Six was intruiging, I wanted to explore the plot and master the hookblade... but then I started exploring the environment.\nThe city of Constantinople is a boring, drab, brown place that would fit in well in a generic African village level, in a generiic FPS. Almost immediately, I began to miss the beauty and majesty of italy; I even missed the underground sections in the Followers of Romulus sections. I slowly lost the desire to touch the game again, and it will probably never be touched a second time. It is condemned to an enternal purgatory, from which I shall never lift it.\nCheers!\n-Camolot", "hours": 9.0, "user_id": "76561198061997939", "username": "Camolot the Creator", "products": 186, "early_access": false}
