{"product_id": "201870", "page": 82, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-30", "text": "Even though this is the most irrelevant Assassin's Creed entirely (main title wise), the gameplay is still fun as the previous titles. The Tower Defense is my favorite part. As one of the biggest fans of Assassin's Creed and one of the most in-depth about it's lore, and being an ex-Moderator on the AC wiki, I only recommend this game to someone who plays AC for the fun of it, even though it's fetch quest simulator in a nutshell. The story is pretty bland, and the only thing we really find out is Ezio's future. That's it.\nYou can literally play all the games except this one and not miss a thing except Desmond waking from his coma.", "hours": 36.8, "username": "Rowdy Uzumaki\u00ae", "products": 201, "early_access": false}
