{"product_id": "201870", "page": 88, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-20", "text": "Aside from having to launch UPlay to play this game that I bought from Steam, the game is actually pretty solid. It's actually the best optimized AC game for the PC that I've played. Which is sad because the last 2 AC games (Black Flag and Unity) are the worst optimized games for the PC. Revelations runs buttery smooth and it's visually appealing. The gameplay is smooth as well. It's just too bad Black Flag (the best game of all them in my opinion) can't run as smoothly as this game (even with an i7 4790K and a GTX 980 Ti - Black Flag and Unity run quite choppy - it's just a sign of poor optimization for PC gamers). If you can get Revelations on sale, get it. It's worth it!", "hours": 2.5, "user_id": "76561198156657129", "username": "VESPA5", "products": 176, "early_access": false}
