{"product_id": "201870", "page": 95, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-31", "text": "Still carries Ezio's charisma, which really helps to make the game but, compared to Brotherhood, Constantinople is from from the beauty of Rome. All in all, a pretty good game with the same old mechanics and some interesting new additions and revelations, no pun intended, story wise. It has been fun Ezio, but it's goodbye.", "hours": 15.3, "user_id": "76561198032977808", "username": "Ragister", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 95, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-30", "text": "I'm a little biased as I love these games but I'll try my best to be impartial.\nYes these games can get a little laborious at times with all the collectibles / side missions but the compelling story, free running and the good mix of stealth to action make this a must play game. Visuals are great as usual for a game of this scale.", "hours": 43.8, "username": "Brainiac Systems", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 95, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-29", "text": "A favorite ending to a favorite hero. Sad and very great story. Join Ezio in his old age as he goes around for one more story. A pretty good AC game\n10/10", "hours": 3.8, "username": "HomestuckCat", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
