{"product_id": "201870", "page": 95, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-23", "text": "Gee... What to say about this one? I'm already running out of ideas and it is only game number 4 out of 14 or so (and I heard complains about the Call of Duty franchise repeating itself).\nEzio \"Manlyman\" Auditore da Firenze de la Jolla Cardinal strikes again - just - not that fast anymore. Ezio struggles a bit since you are playing an very old version of him. He had his best days behind him and still he is able to do all the crazy stuff you did in the other games (Phew! - what an relief).\nEzio already gave the bloodline to the next generation and in the end when you meet the \"spoiler\" you go wandering yourself why a) \"spoiler\" is talking to you and b) how Raymond (main Character... remember) is able to see his Grandfather at this point when the Ani..machine is taking him back to his genetic memorys in the first place if future is not predicted, which if so happen to be would make no sense for any conversation between him and \"spoiler\" in the first place... or maybe I'm just loosing interest and want to play \"Death from above\" on every enemy in the game like before.\n8/10 Is it me or is the gaming-experience getting worse?", "hours": 19.2, "user_id": "76561198036498823", "username": "Solanum nigrum", "products": 1136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 96, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-17", "text": "Asssassin's Creed Revelations isn't that much of a bad game, however, the graphics do feel outdated and the controls on keyboard+mouse feel terrible. Uplay is one of the most terrible gaming services ever devised by man, making it very difficult to start the game. The game will only launch if I open it as administrator, meaning I have to go into the game's files to open the .exe file. Everything is pretty mediocre in this title, but at least you get multiple playable characters. 7/10", "hours": 7.2, "username": "BazzarSpider", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 96, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-16", "text": "The good points are :\n- Good immersion , the life of the game isn't short, the history is just really interesting.\nThe bad points are :\n- Some of the bonus missions are a bit boring, there's some bugs in-game sometimes.", "hours": 24.5, "username": "Dyanek", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
