{"product_id": "201870", "page": 96, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-07", "text": "And here is where Ezio officially overstayed his welcome. The game became a lot more boring, and the story was pretty well defanged. I can recommend it solely for the gameplay which remains entirely unchanged even if they do keep stapling on new things, but the lack of any genuine agency to the story really hurt this game in a big way.\n5/10.", "hours": 13.5, "username": "Doctor Fudge", "products": 1189, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 96, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-07", "text": "Time to review what I consider to be one of the best ways to end an amazing trilogy off in a nice little bow.\nThis game was bought by me during the Ubisoft Weekend Sale whereby I got this game for \u20ac8.99. ($10.13 in USD and \u00a36.64 in British Pound Sterling) When I intially bought the game, it was the Gold Edition meaning that in this review I will include The Lost Archive, Mediterranean Travel Map Pack and The Ancestors Character Pack.\nYou play as Ezio Auditore De Firenze, this time continuing off from where the story left off in Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood whereby it is Ezio's time to travel to Constantinople. With the history of Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad to give Ezio a sense of direction as to what to do and what to discover, he sets off in order to finish off what Alta\u00efr wanted discovered.\nAn excellent game which holds up and has become one of the top best Assassin's Creed games for me. In my opinion, although the gameplay can seem lackluster especially in the multiplayer, this is a game definitely worth playing in your life if you love games with an interesting story topped off with more history than the other editions that came before and character development. I thoroughly enjoyed it and I can't wait to review the other Assassin's Creed games and play the ones I haven't yet. I give Assassin's Creed Revelations a\nand a recommendation to buy it but only with the intent of perhaps buying The Lost Archive and the full game if you think you won't be as invested into the multiplayer as I have.\nThank you so much for reading my review, please give me feedback if any and happy gaming.", "hours": 63.5, "username": "\u2665BonBon", "products": 152, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 96, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-05", "text": "While little in terms of gameplay mechanics were changed, the story in this episode of Ezio's epic journey touched me in ways that few others in the series have.  A beautiful soundtrack certainly doesn't hurt either.", "hours": 15.7, "user_id": "76561197998697330", "username": "DespeBrado", "products": 672, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 97, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-07", "text": "Time to review what I consider to be one of the best ways to end an amazing trilogy off in a nice little bow.\nThis game was bought by me during the Ubisoft Weekend Sale whereby I got this game for \u20ac8.99. ($10.13 in USD and \u00a36.64 in British Pound Sterling) When I intially bought the game, it was the Gold Edition meaning that in this review I will include The Lost Archive, Mediterranean Travel Map Pack and The Ancestors Character Pack.\nYou play as Ezio Auditore De Firenze, this time continuing off from where the story left off in Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood whereby it is Ezio's time to travel to Constantinople. With the history of Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad to give Ezio a sense of direction as to what to do and what to discover, he sets off in order to finish off what Alta\u00efr wanted discovered.\nAn excellent game which holds up and has become one of the top best Assassin's Creed games for me. In my opinion, although the gameplay can seem lackluster especially in the multiplayer, this is a game definitely worth playing in your life if you love games with an interesting story topped off with more history than the other editions that came before and character development. I thoroughly enjoyed it and I can't wait to review the other Assassin's Creed games and play the ones I haven't yet. I give Assassin's Creed Revelations a\nand a recommendation to buy it but only with the intent of perhaps buying The Lost Archive and the full game if you think you won't be as invested into the multiplayer as I have.\nThank you so much for reading my review, please give me feedback if any and happy gaming.", "hours": 63.5, "username": "\u2665BonBon", "products": 152, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
