{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-29", "text": "One of the best in the series. Bridges all the gaps left by Ezio and Altair in a new and fun way.", "hours": 27.8, "username": "Juice", "products": 165, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-28", "text": "OMG great game to have if youre thinking about buying this game I recomend it but after a while it gets kind of repedative.", "hours": 60.0, "user_id": "76561198142383462", "username": "ChayZee", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-28", "text": "Ubisoft clearly has forgotten to develop the gameplay after the succes of ACII. Revelations is exactly the same as Brotherhood, but in a different, far less interesting city. There is not as much to do, the mythology is completely absent, and most of the gameplay is just repeating the one thing over and over again. Revelations is more like ACI than II. The annoying bugs and the gameplay that by now is as rusty as a hundred year old cemetary gate from a bad horror movie, make Revelations into a mediocre game at best.", "hours": 17.9, "user_id": "76561197969316316", "username": "Morthill", "products": 286, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-28", "text": "Game worked, game stopped working. can't play anymore. No support from Ubisoft.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Inardesco", "products": 231, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-25", "text": "I've played AC1, AC2, AC:Brotherhood and AC3 on playstation and quite enjoy all of them. Revelations is the first AC game I got on the PC because it was on sale, and what a let down. The game itself play very similar to other AC titles which I have nothing to complain about but the PC version is buggy as hell. Consider how long this game had been released I can't believe they haven't fixed it and it plays like a bad console port. And Uplay is a pain in the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Aviod.", "hours": 5.4, "user_id": "76561197971977149", "username": "NoobieKuan", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-25", "text": "Having played the previous versions I was quite looking forward to seeing what happened next. Having put about an hours game time into the campaign I am now stuck in the screen where you wander around and get the chance to practice tutorials whilst the game loads. the practice tutorial button changes nothing and the game doesn't load. Don't press anything at all during loading or saving. Whether this is a game problem or a UPlay issue, it's shoddy and not good enough. There isn't the option to load from any previous point, so I will have to start again from the beginning. If I was further through I would be very annoyed. It also has loading issues, don't press anything whilst it's loading. It's not a bad game after all but it has issues which should have been resolved in beta.", "hours": 14.1, "username": "Captain Lump", "products": 218, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-25", "text": "This was my first game in the AC series.\nIt's fun, although I never finished it because I bought AC3 and that was so much better.\nStill had fun with this game, the combat is more detailed and challenging, it just feelt \"small\", after I picked up AC3.\nI may still go back to it, after I finish Black Flag.. if I don't pick up Rogue or Unity right after...", "hours": 24.6, "user_id": "76561198154497341", "username": "JandJguss", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-23", "text": "Uplay servers wasted 5$ off my wallet", "hours": 2.2, "username": "Gumball", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-22", "text": "This game is awesome. The bomb mechanic is really unique, as is the handy Hookblade. Great end to Ezio's trilogy.", "hours": 71.6, "user_id": "76561198093817770", "username": "SergeyMZF", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 102, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-22", "text": "Great campaign. Great graphics. Great open world. Great story. In my opinion the best AC game there is.", "hours": 3.8, "username": "Vulpes, The Creator", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 103, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-22", "text": "From the birth of Ezio Auditore Da Firenze in AC2, to where he lays down his weopons in this one. Great ending to the legendary assassin.\nVery emotional.. but ready to continue the journey of the creed.", "hours": 18.5, "user_id": "76561198076686734", "username": "GR33KWARR10R", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 103, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-22", "text": "The controls on this game are useless for playing on a PC. Often I've got locked into combat or I've just had times when any command is completely ignored. I've killed citizens and I've no idea why, I've died becuase all the suggested commands for breaking combat are useless and don't work. To be honest I'm not even sure I have a clue what the ulitmate point of this game is I seem to get randam missions that didn't seem to fit any real coherent plan. Before anyone asks I have played this for quite some time, or rather I've tried to, I've saved the Sultan's son (or whatever he is) and am currently on some silly mission chasing down a beggar women who even when I catch ON HER OWN WITH NO ONE NEARBY any attempt to hit her results in me killing some randam citizen who suddenly appears in reach. If I hadn't paid so little for this in the Steam sale I'd be demanding a refund.", "hours": 13.0, "user_id": "76561197970610137", "username": "Spooky", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
