{"product_id": "201870", "page": 105, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-03-16", "text": "This game has been out for 4+ years.  I have seen the reviews saying how terrible uPlay is. However, I said to myself \"Surely, after so many years of practice, Ubisoft would have this simple login/database interface working for everyone now...\" and so I installed the game to get it out of my 'to play' queue.\nI am fairly used to being wrong. I have a woman in my life and she lets me know that periodically.  However, I expected to be right in this situation.  I was not which begs the question how does uPlay suck so bad.. and for so long.. one of the (not so) great mysteries of the world.\nWhat confounds me is how a company can take a game that would likely run with no issue in single player mode and insert what would appear to be a simple interface to login and validate your ownership of the game and have that secondary interface cause thousands of players to not be able to actually access the perfectly legitimate, paid for with hard-earned cash game.  That is quite the anti-piracy system.  Makes me sad inside..\n0/10 for making me spend my gaming time today attempting to debug uPlay instead of actually playing a single player game.. and then having to write this silly review griping about uPlay which truly has nothing to with the game itself.\nThe masochist in me is going to insist I try to install this on my desktop machine instead of this gaming laptop.\nIf I do get it to work there.. perhaps I will actually rate the game instead of this POS uPlay...\nThose considering purchasing Ubisoft games beware.", "hours": 42.9, "username": "Halcyon", "products": 395, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 105, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-16", "text": "Despite the weird glitches and sometimes shoddy character design, this game comes through as probably the best one in the series.  It really opens up the story from the Assassin's Creed universe to a huge, detailed, fleshed out universe which is the best immersive experience I may have ever had in a video game.  Sometimes I get mad at some of the weird mechanics and bad design, but overall it is a good game.", "hours": 15.7, "username": "Bartholomew Cubbins", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 105, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "I think Revelations was the most underwhelming game of the series in my opinion. Apart from the shift back to an oriental setting (Constantinopole) which is as excellently designed as always, the game is largely forgettable in terms of substance. There are a few great sequences where you get to play as an aging Altair rather than an aging Ezio but it almost feels as if the developers ran out of story for Ezio before they ran out of game time.\nRevelations was not great, in my opinion, but still good if by this point you're still with the series. It's more of the same, but mostly in a good way.", "hours": 51.3, "username": "PaulP", "products": 666, "early_access": false}
