{"product_id": "201870", "page": 108, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-20", "text": "So this is the first Assasins Creed game I decided to play on PC, considering I usually play it on XBOX. My experience at the beginng with Uplay was awful. Ubisofts pc ports suck. I signed into a account where they never told me it got deactavited, so I had to Unlink uplay, uninstall uplay, reinstall uplay, uninstall the game, and reinstall the game. Yeah. Thanks Ubishit.\nThe game it self\nGreat game! Awesome story, great fighting, good graphics, and cool weapons. Its a great AC game! Has everything you want out of Assassins Creed. Ezio is as always a badass.\nThe Game itself: 96/100 Desmonds\nUbisoft: 1/8 IGN too much uplay", "hours": 13.8, "user_id": "76561198132382645", "username": "hiroller", "products": 33, "found_funny": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 108, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-19", "text": "This review is subjective and entirely my own opinion, feel free to agree or disagree with it.\nI love the Assassin's Creed franchise, but this is by far the weakest link in its chain. It feels like Ubisoft took everything that made AC: Brotherhood great and then added a few new features that drag the game down.\nI haven't tried the multiplayer (I never really liked MP in AC) but I imagine the multiplayer is dead given the age of the game.\nThere is probably a few things that I have missed but I would only recommend this game if you are a fan of the series and you want to see a conclusion to two of the best protagonists in the franchise. I would only buy it if it is on sale, it may be worth \u00a314.99 but I would wait until Steam has a sale, where you could pick it up for around \u00a33.75.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "\ud835\udd6f\ud835\udcf8\ud835\udcc1\ud835\udcc1\u05e5\ud83c\udfac\ud83c\udfa5\ud835\udce9\ud835\udd94\ud835\udd94\ud835\udcdc", "products": 542, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 108, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-19", "text": "The fitting \"end\" to the Ezio Auditore da Firenze story! Also, You'll get the final chapter to Altair. The best game of the trilogy by far! By the way, check the movie that was made for the last days os Ezio.", "hours": 21.9, "username": "Korvo", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 108, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-18", "text": "Great game. Multiplayer was fun back in the day but servers are barren now.", "hours": 69.3, "username": "GBP", "products": 545, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-18", "text": "Unfortuantly I can't comment on the game content because the game won't launch... There seems to be a problem with the ubisoft launcher and steam can't start the game. I was really looking forward to playing and was very dissaponted, I don't think I'll be purchasing any more Ubisoft games in the future.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198053407501", "username": "zanna", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-17", "text": "3rd favorite assasins creed game last one worth playing", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561198026394897", "username": "hulaboy616", "products": 350, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-17", "text": "Just getting into the AC franchise and the Ezio trilogy is great!  I just did story mode so I could get to the other games.  Graphics good, storyline also good.  There is a lot to do in this game that I didn't explore much.  Den battles, assassin recruits, etc.  I was pretty much entertained with the story and like I said, I wanted to get to the other AC games.", "hours": 14.7, "username": "regalunicorn420", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-16", "text": "Great end of the stories of Ezio Auditore da Firenze and Altair Ibn-La'Ahad.\nAnyone who loves tale of Ezio must own also this game.\nThere is action, love, betray and BOMBS. With bombs you can enjoy a lot of fun. Also some missions on 100% synchronization are challenging!", "hours": 24.8, "username": "Grizz", "products": 392, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-16", "text": "ACRev is continuing from the ACBro which the story of the ancestor tell us now Ezio is going in adventure to reveal what Altair has left behind, as for Desmond, he is being trapped inside his mind after kiling Lucy in ACBro.\nIt's definitely level up from the ACBro in terms of gameplay. Now you have many arsenal of weapon in your hand to assasinate the enemy. But, from the money to get mechanic is the same from ACII and ACBro.\nAnd in this ACRev, you will know Desmond's past and what happen to Altair after he defeat Al Mualim.\nI really recommended this game to other fan of AC and to all of you who want to play it. Even though Ezio is becoming old, his skill as an assassin's is getting more polished.\nSo it's definitely worth to try.", "hours": 26.0, "username": "Venterivia", "products": 446, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-15", "text": "good", "hours": 31.6, "username": "famasan", "products": 393, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-15", "text": "Other people dislike this part of Ezio's story, but it was one of my favourites. It came to a sad ending but gave an awesome conclusion to Ezio's life as an assassin.", "hours": 19.5, "username": "Dibblez", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-14", "text": "A beautiful game with an excellent story, gameplay and immersiveness. I did only the main quests and enjoyed this game very much. I felt it was the best of the series up to this stage. Give it a try just for the story and visuals.", "hours": 18.1, "username": "Squashbuckler", "products": 415, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-11", "text": "Game is aweisome i must be a LAGGI \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 well assassins creed or far cry dosent lag at all!! its perfect its a bit slow words but its alwais worth it having it and not lagging like Goat Simulator i have very low GB but this game dosent make me lag,\nAt the starting of the game i love it just that im a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing retard at the game and dnk how to \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 to play it but its realy nice having a game that wont make problems i found some straing stuff that where funny and VERY aweisome kills but i kinda starting to hate it not the game but multyplayer not becose BAD MT! no becose peopel kil me wen i got them first that soo \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing annoying but hey atleast it is fun playing Story Mode thats fun! allot of fun peopel must play other AS becose the unity one is still cool 60 are worth it or meaby becose they cant fin the key for playing the game its easy... i dint knew neiter but i know how peopel that dnk just tipe too me and il explain :)", "hours": 61.9, "user_id": "76561198123159846", "username": "SaraLuna", "products": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 109, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-10", "text": "I am a huge Assasins Creed nerd. Ive loved the series all the way until this latest one, but that is besides the point. My personal opinion is that Revelations and II are the best ones in the series. For the parkour, for the combat, for the story. It all works very well together and the progression throughout the game really makes playing enjoyable!", "hours": 97.0, "username": "Sneaky Cruise", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-07", "text": "Stabbing people and stealing their money to jumping around on the roof murduring guards, this game is fun and probably the best of the franchise.\n9.5/10 some hard controls but still super fun", "hours": 14.2, "username": "L CappyTan", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-05", "text": "This was the last real Assassin's Creed game. It brought the legends of Altair and Ezio together and wrapped up both their stories in a satisfying climax.", "hours": 21.5, "user_id": "76561198001251133", "username": "Sledge Hammer!", "products": 258, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-02", "text": "Game is great, but the thing is that you need to watch out for. Its uplay it can screw you over in several ways. Once you fix uplay, you have to make sure that your saves are not deleted. So back up your saves, again and again and again, with each break or at intervals. As that is what happened to me, saves got deleted.", "hours": 50.3, "username": "TebrasD", "products": 105, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-29", "text": "What brotherhood did wrong, Revelations does right. the boring minigames are less boring, the overworld is more interesting and the villens and writing are on par with the first. as well as seeing the main character being a well seasoned veteren of an assassin and watching him be tired of his life. fallowing a single man through his life as an assassin and watching how it affects him as he goes from a young gigalo to a jaded gray hair was the most enjoyable part of this game set for me. and with all this game DOES improve over Brotherhood does make this worth a purchase.", "hours": 31.4, "username": "\u0418\u0243\u023e", "products": 284, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-26", "text": "Another Assassin's Creed game!\nI will never stop fawning about the masterpiece that is Assassin's Creed 2, and Brotherhood was a nice touchdown celebration/victory lap for all the fans of AC2. However, Revelations is the third game on the same character who already did all his most important stuff in AC2, and the pilot of that character who is now trapped in a recursive stack overflow and has to do unneccesary tasks to regain his body.\nGameplay is unchanged from AC2 and Brotherhood, with the exception of some horrible first person platformers that you can more or less ignore, and a tower defense game that you really only have to do once. Istanbul/Constantinople in the 16th century was an exciting place where cool stuff happened but you really don't get much of a feeling of that. The open sprawling area of rome where you can ride horses into battle in the streets is gone, the main characters have little to add and the ending that the entire game builds to from the end of the tutorial is little more than a rambling introspection.\nIn short, the game is good but is a pile of wasted potential.", "hours": 19.3, "username": "Tomfoolery", "products": 455, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-25", "text": "Probably the most re-playable assassin's creed game ever made. If you love the assassins creed series then this is for you the stories not great and some things are a bit wonky but if you like a generic assassins creed game that has very regular randomly generated events then this is for you", "hours": 47.8, "username": "Boxwithsmiley", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-24", "text": "10/10\nPLUS: Great ending to the saga of Altair and Ezio. Beautiful graphics of Istanbul, amazing characters and very cool missions. The ending is absolutely perfect, creative and touching!\nGame runs smoothly of my PC and looks better than AC3 and Black Flag withot high tech requirement!\nMINUS: The game doesn't improve anything nor does it add fresh things, but it doesn't have to. It continues the saga and give a perfect finish to the story of previous AC games.", "hours": 18.6, "user_id": "76561198096659530", "username": "tomek.nowobilski", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-24", "text": "buy the assassin's creed revelations - gold edition is very good for some guys love to looks cool and kill a lot", "hours": 69.7, "username": "\u2721Protocol7-Hassan\u2721", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-24", "text": "7 out of 10\nAnother Assassins Creed episode.  This one sees Etzio Auditore travel to Istanbul to recover keys.  The keys will unlock Altair's library.  As always you are Desmond Miles reliving history captured in his genes.\nIn short if you liked previous Assassins Creed episodes then you will like this one.  There is a lot to like but also a lot to hate intensely.  It really feels like this game could have been so much better.\nThe good:\n1. For the first time I actually liked Etzio as character.  In fact all characters are quite likeable except Desmond who continues to be a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\n2. In general stuff to do, unlock, collect and missions.\nThe bad:\n3. Istanbul is a sad destination compared to colorful Italy before.\n4. You constantly have to send your assassin allies to take on missions in foreign cities.  It becomes quite a pain to constantly search for a pigeon loft.\n5. Control training is not available on command.  If you are lucky you can catch a specific type of training while the game loads.\n6. Very little about the story behind the story.  Also no Abstergo puzzles, a highlight for me in previous games.\n7. The game was too long to keep my attention.\nThe ugly:\n8. Unfortunately like previous Assassins Creed episodes, combat is pathetic.  I attack a highlighted enemy however Etzio/Altair would rather attack my ally next to the enemy.  Also if an ally stands next to an enemy when you passionate him your ally will be caught in a double assignation.\n9. The new \"history\" garbage played out in 1st person mode.  What twaddle is this?  Only for masochists.\n10. Screen flashing the PC desktop.", "hours": 33.9, "user_id": "76561197994281375", "username": "Harm", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 110, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-23", "text": "Fell from 50 feet as a ragdoll, survived with no damage taken.\n420/69\nWould fall again.", "hours": 50.6, "username": "My dick is a wizard", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-23", "text": "story is very good. you should play first game of assassins creed game series. then brotherhood you should buy it. graphics are better than brotherhood. multiplayer is amazing. if you buy this game, you will play this game with very good story and magnificent sights of istanbul or constantinople", "hours": 36.6, "username": "enessfk", "products": 68, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-22", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Revelations is a step up from the previous Assassin's Creed games.\nIt includes new climbing and freerunning movements and new equipment such as the hook blade and parachutes.\nThe game is well written and is a perfect and climatic end to Ezio's story.\nThe customization aspect of the game is still in the opening stages compared to the more recent AC games but grasps the concepts that you want in customization with upgrades as well as visual improvments such as different colour sets to choose from.\nAlongside Ezio's journey there is also the continuation of Desmond's with added and explained lore and more truths about the Animus, Templars and Assassins, as there has been with the previous AC games.", "hours": 4.3, "user_id": "76561198119477842", "username": "Bantom of the Opera", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-19", "text": "\"The Hookblade has two parts. The hook and the blade.\"\n10/10 Mind blowing revelation.", "hours": 18.9, "username": "Samekichi Kiseki", "products": 109, "found_funny": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-19", "text": "What a game!! ..TOP gameplay, a little easy, but if you dont buy new weapons its not too easy ;) a must have for fans of the series..it completes the storyline of AC1 and AC2 if you didnt play it it wont be such a \"revelation\" ;)...to me its the best part of the series...best controls, best sound/musik, very good characters and best story till the end.. a must have", "hours": 25.9, "username": "moa-deep", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-18", "text": "This game is boring and the controls are really convoluted. I honestly don't know why this franchise is so popular. The controls are just horrible.\nIt's also broken. Another terrible PC port that belongs on consoles. In the single player campaign, none of the cinematics work properly. I guess there is a fix for it, but I can't see wasting more than 15 seconds on this game.\nThe multiplayer was unique, but the novelty wore off quickly. I would pass on this one.", "hours": 6.9, "user_id": "76561198012620303", "username": "meoget", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-18", "text": "..", "hours": 11.1, "username": "Mad Mask", "products": 88, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-16", "text": "Assassins Creed is one of the best games out there today. The moultiplayer part of AC is boring but  the single player makes playing for this game worth it. The storyline is on going from the original AC so  if your new to this game you might wish to google the story line unless you bought them all.\n10/10", "hours": 76.3, "username": "Pistashio", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 111, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-16", "text": "The finale of the Ezio Auditore saga. Ezio, now a maestro assassin, travels to Constantinople in search of Altair's secrets to fight the templar \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s. Recommended!", "hours": 36.4, "username": "Nasty Pirate", "products": 844, "early_access": false}
