{"product_id": "201870", "page": 112, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-15", "text": "AKA Ezio's fun trip to Constantinople. They added Plants vs Zombies and Portal to this Assassin's Creed game for some reason. If you like stabbing people, owning your own businesses and jumping into bushes, this game has it in spades. Plays a lot like AC2 and Brotherhood though, so hopefully you liked those games.", "hours": 18.5, "username": "JasonTerminator", "products": 829, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 112, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-15", "text": "I must say, this game is absolutely fantastic! The graphics are amazing even on a low setting and the gameplay is up to Assasins Creed standard. My only downside to the game is Uplay, which seemed like it wanted me to play the game since Uplay kept crashing for no reason and I could'nt play AC revelations without Uplay. Took a while to get it working.\nI think AC Revelations is THE best game from the series along with Black Flag.\n10/10 For the game\n-100,000,000/10 for Uplay", "hours": 53.9, "username": "\u03bbctionwill65", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 112, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-15", "text": "I know I go it very late but it still remains one great game. I really enjoy the parts where you play Altair", "hours": 28.3, "user_id": "76561198151568497", "username": "\u272a Don't Dead Open Inside", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 112, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-15", "text": "8.5/10\nAnother amazing addition to the series, one that ends the stories of both Altair Ibn La-Ahad & Ezio Auditore da Firenze.\nStory is very compelling and worth playing for. Gameplay has not changed from the last two Assassin's Creed games but improves on them with more gameplay elements including a hookblade, bombs, and other assortments. A lot of things makes a return from the previous Assassin's Creed games such as a brotherhood, brotherhood missions, renovating cities, collecting items scattered throughout the whole game and ofcourse, synchronization points. Worth buying in my opinion.", "hours": 2.0, "username": "Vixus", "products": 192, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 112, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-12", "text": "My only complain is that IT DOESN'T WORK. The new things that Ubisoft is doing to \"protect\" itself it just screws up the loading of the game, it doesn't even open for me, it worked for a good while, but then suddenly nothing, the Ubisoft client doesn't update, and then you can't play your damn game.", "hours": 9.1, "username": "Grandma", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
