{"product_id": "201870", "page": 114, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "While the singleplayer may fall in the shadow of 2 and Brotherhood, it is still a great game to play. The multiplayer is fun even if slightly unbalanced for new players, and it runs well on medium hardware. Probably the last well optimized AC game for PC.", "hours": 69.4, "username": "Turboblaze", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 114, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-28", "text": "I really LOVED AC2 and Brotherhood. I spent hours just watching the cities and landmarks, enjoying the cutscenes like a movie. Revelations had some big shoes to fill and I\nwasn t dissapointed.\nPROS\n- Istambul is as beautiful as Firenze, Rome or Venice, but in its own way so it does not get old.\n- Gameplay is already very proved and polished. Not too much to say about it, same old with a few tweaks.\n- Solid story and interesting NPCs help make some proved mechanics still fun to play. Even sidequests usually are connected with the main story. Ezzio is getting old. He\ngets tired, his back hurts and the young ladies don\u00b4t pay him the attention they used to. But even that is something he does with charm.\n- Tower Defense minigames are fun to play, but dont happen often (finished the game with two)\nCONS\n- A few too many weapons and tools that aren\u00b4t really useful: The crossbow made the knives obsolete; crafting bombs can be fun, but make no real difference; no real use for parachutes, handgun or poison.\n- Desmond missions are not fun at all.", "hours": 41.6, "user_id": "76561198073966893", "username": "Nalliendraug", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 114, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "click on ppl as a stealthy assassin blah blah blah u already know what this game is about when u clicked on it", "hours": 1.9, "username": "Lil' Ling", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 115, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "Fun game i love it its amazing to play and you lose count of time playing it!", "hours": 31.9, "user_id": "76561198119749088", "username": "MaryBrowns", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 115, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "It has a bad reputation for being the worse game in the series but I thought I owed it to Ezio to complete his amazing trilogy and I am glad I did.\nThe map isn't as large as the other Ezio games but they make up for it by having plenty of extra missions, quests and collectables.\nIf you are thinking of skipping out this game, don't, because it is well worth a play and has a brilliant storyline with characters that you become emotionally involved with.", "hours": 23.0, "username": "Jacob", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 115, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Not much new here. Fun parkour but only for a little while.", "hours": 17.3, "username": "Doc. Cocktanium", "products": 252, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 115, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Assassin`s Creed Revelations- this is the final chapter of Ezio Auditore adventures, and you going explore the last actions of Al-Tair.\n- \"Hookblade\", a new balde that help you to climb.\n- By using the \"hookblde\" you can across buldings with \"Ziplines\", this is one of the GREAT new features in Revelations.\n- You can do assassination from zipline.\n- Now you can make grneades, there is a large selections of grenades that you can make.\nbut first, you need finde the commodities by open boxes.\n- The combat system improved and now there are some new \"combo kills\".\n- Slow motion animation added when you kill someone.\n- New weapons and suits.\n+ Awesome graphics for 2011.\n+ Great sound effects and background music.\n+ The texture of the environment is so nice and impressive.\n+ The models looking great.\n+ The parkour is great with the \"Hookblade\".\n+ Great story.\n10/10\nRevelations, a great ending for Ezio Auditore trilogy, and during the game you will switch sometimes to \"Altair flashbacks\", and you will discover the last actions in his life.\nGreat game!\nI'm recommend this game.", "hours": 36.8, "username": "lofty", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 115, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Great game", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561197999008607", "username": "sd_sergiopeixoto", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 115, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Cool story, cool setting, cool new things to do and new weapons to your arsenal. I'd give it a 9/10, because it is too short for my taste. I fully played brotherhood in 40 hours, 2 in 30 hours and this one in 26, so it's a little smaller.\nBut nonetheless it's a very epic game with amazing graphics.\nSadly it is the end of the story of Ezio and Alta\u00efr. But they've worked it out brilliantly, good work Ubisoft.", "hours": 26.5, "user_id": "76561198136535820", "username": "Bobbe", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
