{"product_id": "201870", "page": 116, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-14", "text": "Boy oh boy this is a really good game it may be short compared to Assassin's creed brotherhood, but it still immerses the player in a good storyline marking the end of Ezio's past. I'd reccomend this game for any Assassin's creed fan or just a gamer in general", "hours": 24.5, "user_id": "76561198049815749", "username": "\u0295\u2022\u1d25\u2022\u0294 Androshi", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 117, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-14", "text": "Possibly the best game of the \"Ezio Saga\", because of the evolution of the main character. The game doesn't bring big changes like Assasin's Creed 2, but it improves on it and Constantinople is a very interesting city to develop the final chapter of ezio. It is especially recommended after playing the two previous games to be able to enjoy it on it's fullest.", "hours": 172.4, "user_id": "76561198023019965", "username": "Pablo", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 117, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-14", "text": "Don't listen to people who say that the game is too easy and dull. If you finish every single mission with 100% sync, the game becomes 20 times more fun to play.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "unknown", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 117, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-14", "text": "Assassin's Creed Revelations it's good game.\nSingle-player:\nYou got new location - it's Constantinople (Istanbul now), weps from Assassin's Creed Brotherhood and few new: new knife-hook for the right hand, to much bombs: bomb-thorns, bomb-bait, poison bombs and so on (same time here we are can select battle tactics), not long story but very interesting (mine time 17 hours). We are will got more about Altair and him life; open world, but not big - two Islands (one city). About graphic: this game was make few countries like France, Ukraine and so on. They are make new nice Assassin's Creed game, that graphic to much better, but to much colors at Turkish outfits. That bad to my eyes ^ ^\nHere Ezio find new girl :3 They are will live long and happy <3 Cos she is redhead (all redheads is cutie<3).\nHere no sluttie at city ^ ^ only Gipsy :D\nMultiplayer:\nAssassin's Creed Revelations it's second game of Assassin's Creed which got multiplayer. Not much chars for select how was it in Assassin's Creed Brotherhood and few maps. New gameplay: several new game modes for multiplayer (to much interesting).\nGraphic at multiplayer looks not perfect like at single-player.", "hours": 17.3, "username": "\u01b8\u04c1\u01b7 Bunny Girl \u01b8\u04c1\u01b7", "products": 573, "found_funny": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 117, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "Pretty much Brotherhood with more bombs.\nI got it on sale for five bucks so I don't really mind.  The combat is more or less the same but with more gory killmoves. Overall, I find the game way too easy and there's all this extra stuff thrown in but I never wound up using any of it because it's always easier to just stab everyone than to attempt any stealth or diversion tactics.\nThe story kinda straight up sucks. It's over before it really begins and I didn't really even care when (no spoilers) one of the plot essential characters died near the end of the game because he only appeared for like a half hour of screentime total. It was also somewhat hard to follow, and I didn't feel like any of it really mattered to Ezio's goal. On the bright side, Altair's story (what little of it there was) was great, though I was somewhat let down by the fact that Altair never wears the armor he made (the invincible armor from AC2).\nThe map is very bland as well. It's nothing but building after building with a river separating 1/5 of the map from everything else.\nI'd recommend this game only if it's on sale, your first assassin's creed, or if you just want to finish Ezio's and/or Altair's story. Otherwise, I wouldn't bother.", "hours": 69.0, "username": "Fine", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 117, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "See my review of Assassin's Creed. This is one of the \"Italian\" Assassin's Creed games. What can I say? Great characterization and story, wonderful sense of time and place. I's like Tombraider in Ranaissance italy. Next to Assassin's Creed: Black Flag this is a favourtie of the series.", "hours": 51.6, "username": "Ginger Baker", "products": 385, "early_access": false}
