{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-28", "text": "Neue Stadt zum Rumlaufen, neue Story, gleicher Held, gleiches Gameplay - AC Revelations zusammengefasst.\nPunkt I: Die Stadt - Konstantinopel / Istanbul\nWie f\u00fcr Assassin's Creed \u00fcblich, eine wunderh\u00fcbsch animierte, lebendig wirkende Welt mit Passanten, Marktschreiern, Wachen, H\u00e4ndlern - allem was eine Assassin's Creed-Stadt eben so braucht. Historisch und proportional korrekt nachgebaut, kommt sofort das tolle \"Jaaaaaaa-hier-darf-ich-rumlaufen-Gef\u00fchl auf\". Sehr gut gelungen.\nPunkt II: Die Story - Gut gelungen, wenn auch kurz\nKurz und knapp wie auch schon in Brotherhood erz\u00e4hlt Revelations eine vergleichsweise gute, schn\u00f6rkellose Geschichte, wobei es den gr\u00f6\u00dften Nachteil aus AC II nicht wieder ins Spiel bringt. Ein zwei Twists sind auch mit dabei - alles in allem f\u00fcr ein AC-Spiel wirklich angemessen.\nPunkt III: Der Held - Ezio\nGleiche Animationen, nur 2 neue Tricks (Hakenklinge im Kampf und Hakenklinge bei der Fortbewegung) - Ezio hat sich nicht viel ver\u00e4ndert, nur dass er jetzt halt um die 50 Jahre alt ist. Seine Kampftechnik beeinflusst das nicht, im Gegenteil, er lernt sogar noch brutalere und assassinigere (ist das ein Wort?) Killmoves. #\nSein Charakter bleibt auch nicht auf der Strecke, denn seine freundliche, inzwischen nat\u00fcrlich weisere Art wird angemessen, aber nicht \u00fcbertrieben betont.\nPunkt IV: Das Gameplay\nWie Schon in Punkt III erw\u00e4hnt, so hat sich das Gameplay nur um 2 Tricks erweitert - Die beiden Eigenschaften der Hakenklinge, die man f\u00fcr's Klettern, f\u00fcr's Seilrutschen und f\u00fcr's Hinterh\u00e4ltig-t\u00f6ten nutzen kann.\nDeutlich st\u00e4rker macht einen das nicht, aber wann waren der Kampf oder das Klettern in Assassin's Creed schon schwierig? Das einzige was es tut, ist cool aussehen und sein, und die Steuerung ein wenig erleichtern - was es wohl auch soll.\nFazit:\nObwohl die Steuerung, die Grafik, und das generelle Gameplay sich nicht im Geringsten von den beiden Vorg\u00e4ngern AC II und AC: Brotherhood unterscheiden, so ist doch AC: Revelations f\u00fcr seine 15\u20ac auf jeden Fall lohnenswert. Eine Kaufempfehlung f\u00fcr AC-Fans und Neulinge!", "hours": 28.9, "user_id": "76561198098730481", "username": "gebargel", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-27", "text": "After 37 hours of Assassin\u2019s Creed Revelations, this game is amazing just like any other Assassin\u2019s Creed game! Though, not as good as 3 or Brotherhood, far better then the first. I truly enjoyed and it was far more cinematic than the other games before it. Though, I did have one problem with it and that was there was not as much to do compared to 3 or Brotherhood. More than 1 or 2 but still not enough. I still highly recommend this game to anyone for sure! The Lost Archive DLC (last two pictures) were really really shocking if you pay any attention to the main modern story line.", "hours": 39.9, "username": "Sully", "products": 567, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-27", "text": "I love all the new features added into this game, double the fun and the awesomeness of this series. Insanely cool! x)", "hours": 18.1, "user_id": "76561198094927737", "username": "Stary", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-26", "text": "If you like Assassins Creed and Ezio in particular, then you'll enjoy this game.\nGraphics 8/10\nSound 8/10\nCombat 10/10\nInterface 6/10\nMuch of the same in way of mechanics a few tweaks here and there but if you play Assassins creed you'll adapt quickly.\nMulti player is robust and enjoyable if its your type of thing.\nThere is tons of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665to do just like the previous games, so have fun.\nGraphics are solid.\nSound is solid.\nStory is well its Ezio.", "hours": 5.6, "user_id": "76561198060704337", "username": "Trippnfool", "products": 168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-26", "text": "You can play a lute.\n10/10", "hours": 26.3, "username": "Tomman23", "products": 235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-18", "text": "Revelations again comes off the heels of its predecessor Brotherhood and improves on many things from it. The hookblade is easily the greatest addition, improving climbing speed, maneuverability and gameplay. Other new additions such as bombs are all woven into the storyline very well and make sense. More compelling characters, fantastic music, and visuals, along with a nice change of scenery from Italy, are all welcome.\nI would only say that it lacks a really detestable villain, like Brotherhood had, and not -quite- as many interesting supporting characters, however, still entertaining. Even the tower defense minigame is strange in this series, but fun. All in all it's a fantastic adventure with challenges and goals, with some clever and satisfying revelations, both to Ezio and Desmond.\nWell recommended for if you enjoyed AC2 / Brotherhood. Wouldn't recommend it to new players of the series however. That's about it.", "hours": 53.1, "username": "Fluff-Kevlar", "products": 518, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 132, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-17", "text": "Completed the storyline element of this game in roughly two weekends of gameplaplay, so a bit short for my liking. Ezio's finale was also slightly dissapionting. If you have played the previous games , needless to say, playing this one is a must.", "hours": 14.5, "username": "the_chris_g", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
