{"product_id": "201870", "page": 136, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-16", "text": "\u542f\u793a\u5f55\u4e2d\u7684E\u53d4\uff0c\u6709\u70b9\u771f\u6b63\u7684\u50cf\u4e2a\u5148\u77e5\u4e86\n\u6e38\u620f\u4e2d\u8dd1\u8df3\u7684\u65f6\u5019\uff0c\u53ef\u4ee5\u6e05\u6670\u7684\u542c\u5230Ezio\u7684\u5598\u6c14\n\u5e74\u9f84\u7684\u589e\u957f\uff0c\u8ba9Ezio\u7684\u4f53\u529b\u4e0b\u964d\n\u5374\u4e5f\u662f\u5bf9\u4eba\u751f\u7684\u611f\u609f\u8d8a\u6765\u8d8a\u591a\u7684\u65f6\u671f\n\u6700\u540e\u5bf9\u7d22\u83f2\u4e9a\u9610\u91ca\u523a\u5ba2\u4fe1\u6761\u7684\u610f\u4e49\nTo say that nothing is true, is to realize that the foundations of society are fragile, and that we must be the shepherds of our own civilization\uff1b\nTo say that everything is permitted, is to understand that we are the architects of our actions, and we must live with their consequences, whether glorious or tragic.\n\u8fd9\u65f6\u5019\u7684Ezio\u771f\u6b63\u7684\u662f\na kind of teacher\uff0ca mentor", "hours": 40.3, "username": "Yaksa", "products": 274, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 136, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-14", "text": "Loved this game way more than Brotherhood. To this point in the series I would rank this game just behind Assassin's Creed II. It seems as though all the extra missions that were thrown into Brotherhood have been toned down. I found myself wanting to liberate towers and open all the shops because it seemed like there were less of them this go around. The Ezio/Altair stories were tied in together nicely and at the end of the game seemed to satisfy the conclusions to their story. On the other side of the story though, the Desmond portion was confusing before and even more confusing at the end. Overall though, I highly recommend this game along with the second one.", "hours": 12.5, "username": "dzinction", "products": 360, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 136, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-13", "text": "After not playing an Assassin's Creed game for a fair few months I was looking forward to getting stuck into another. There isn't much I can say about Revelations which hasn't already been said before.\nIt carries the same weight as the previous games in the serious, the combat mechanics are almost identical. You can pull off some real fancy counters with some even more satisfying sounds.\nYou have to have played some of the previous games to understand much of the story but you can try and pick it up as you go. I only finished the main story and that lasted me about 15 hours, and there is still opportunity to play the side missions, do all the optional stuff afterwards to, I would expect you can wrack up 20 hours+ in Revelations if you wanted to span it out as far as possible.\nCan't go wrong with this title.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "Tom", "products": 2956, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
