{"product_id": "201870", "page": 136, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-08", "text": "I totally love the AC series but this game is beyond redemption . So many bugs and so many glitches , not attended by Uplay or ubisoft or whatsoever . Lost 3 chapters of gameplay due to a craash and uplay not being able to restore the cloud saves , constatnt crashes , that make attempting to 100% the game basicly impossible. I was optimistic about uplay! at some point but now i despise it even more then GFWL seriously ubisoft start paying attention to the games and no attention to support , or you're gonna turn into EA at some point . You platform really sucks beyond comparison. It's sad that I'm considering not playing a certain game just cause it runs through uplay..... Get your\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665straight", "hours": 45.7, "user_id": "76561198066285039", "username": "Shadowgrimmm", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-07", "text": "AVOID LIKE THE PLAGUE. I am literally unable to run it due to the DRM complaining about my CD key even though I have never run it before on any other. It seems Ubisoft tries their hardest to make all their games as difficult as possible (or even outright impossible) to run. Save yourself a mountain of hassle and buy a game that *just* plays without all this unnecessary DRM nonsense that you don't even need because I'm running it through steam anyway (you'd think they'd be authentication enough).", "hours": 39.9, "username": "doubledispatch", "products": 206, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
