{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-06", "text": "Assassins Creed Revelations continues the story of Etzio, though aged, still has his talents as the great assassin. You are thrown into many different environments. Scaling buildings, fighting opponents, and managing your brotherhood is easier, than ever. Ubisoft adds a few kinks so that things aren\u2019t too easy that is. Defending your Den\u2019s from attack, adds a defensive gameplay to the game, which has never really been done before in any previous AC game. The story is just as compelling as the last, with stunning visuals to lead the way. Soldiers can counter, your counter adding some interesting fights, as not all enemies can just be killed with a thrust of a sword, or axe. And on top of that multiplayer has improved as well. The game is once again a must buy. This story is definitely something you won\u2019t forget.", "hours": 14.5, "user_id": "76561198008241330", "username": "Petroph", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-05", "text": "Wow", "hours": 17.0, "user_id": "76561198014933683", "username": "Doopers", "products": 109, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-04", "text": "Not nearly as long as AssII or AssBro, but still a vital piece to the puzzle that is the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665series. I found the addition to fill in the backstory between the original and this title to ber thoroughly engaging and entertaining. The economic side of the game is rather weak with a buggy income system that resets the income timer every time you start or finish any mission. But it's easily worked around, and as I alluded to earlier, the storyline was well done.\nA great purchase for fans of the series, short but worth any sale price!", "hours": 44.4, "username": "{RiP}Biggs", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-04", "text": "This game is crap\nEDIT: I fixed the bug and now its epic !", "hours": 21.4, "user_id": "76561198113688960", "username": "nfinity4", "products": 174, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-03", "text": "This is a well-done PC port. It launches in native resolution, chooses sane graphics options and changes ALL of the user interface accordingly whether you're using keyboard and mouse or a controller. You'll have to manually install Uplay in order for it to launch, but at least Uplay doesn't prevent it from working, unlike other Ubisoft titles.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198050504492", "username": "Srs Bisnis", "products": 139, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-02", "text": "Say AC2 was the greatest one of Ezio's trilogy, Revelations is the most user-friendly.\nI played this game twice, that the second was right after seeing the end of the story.The whole story mainly happens in Istanbul,which may be the largest city AC series ever has, even larger than Rome.\nThe background music is as good as epic, adding a lot emotion to cutscenes. Especially the main theme beginning with a female chanting.It is tremendously beautiful and echos in my brain over and over.\nDuring the play, Altair's life after Al-Mualim's death is revealed. It is pretty much the same story told by AC novels, so it didn't surprise me. The amazing part is when Ezio finally \"meet\" Altair, face to face, well, sort of. I felt the sorrow and joy across hundreds of years between those two masters. It did feel like witnessing the history.\nEzio's story may be over, but that of the assassins continues.", "hours": 9.4, "user_id": "76561198099180267", "username": "soldadad", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 137, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "not a bad game, why vote down? bcs of the Uplay. i bought this game for single player, when i start it up the game hast to check for updates. OK, but isn't it a bit old to recieve updates? and it takes quite long. than the Uplay launcher starts, WITH UPDATING! when i click play, i wanna play. not some stupid launcher update from what has nothing to do with the game itself! im actually writing this while Uplay is updating..\nAND NOW ITS LOADING THE GAME INFORMATION WHICH ALREADY FAILED ONCE AND NOW IS GOING ON FOR LIKE 10 MINUTES, I don't wanna waste my spare time for some stupid game infromation to load!", "hours": 3.3, "username": "tbeest", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
