{"product_id": "201870", "page": 139, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-27", "text": "People often wonder whether AC R. is worth the money given that is doesn't add in to any great extent to the AC series but to  those people I say please just splash out. As the subtitle suggests, the game brings greater clarity to the overall storyline of AC and adds insight into Ezio and Altair. The gameplay is recognisable and clean and there is a greater graphical clean-ness. The storyline is interesting and enjoyable and adds new weapons and armour. No, the game isn't a necessity to the series but is still and 9/10 for me.", "hours": 27.9, "username": "PraetorianElite", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 139, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed Revelations is a great game. It is not flawless, but the story and the gameplay is really good. Such a great feeling when stabbing a guard or a Templar from behind. I can assure you you will learn a lot about Istanbul and Ottoman period playing this game alone. Revelations was my first experiance with Assassin's Creed franchise. I spent 29 entertaining hours on this game and now other Creed games are waiting for me: \"Nothing is true, everything is permitted.\"", "hours": 29.1, "username": "avdibeg", "products": 266, "early_access": false}
