{"product_id": "201870", "page": 139, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "This installment in the series ties all the previous games into a single cohesive story line.\nNot being a fan of multiplayer games, Revelations is in someways the best game in the series, as after this title the games focus seemed to be more towards the multiplayer aspect. I've played and enjoyed III and Black Flag (Which is a total departure from any of the previous games). They are always decent. In terms of story though, Revelations marked a high point in the Creed games, that I've yet to see another one achieve.\nOverall 7.5/10   (in my ratings \"5\" is the base line and is a \"OK\" game)\nGraphics: 8/10 (At time of release)\nSound: 5/10   (Music and Effects)\nVoice Acting: 7/10\nStory: 9/10\nGameplay: 8/10", "hours": 48.8, "user_id": "76561197970728484", "username": "Solitaire", "products": 2090, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 139, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Aside from the Ubisoft drm (why I don't have many hours played on steam), this game was probably one of the best for it's series, the noteriety system was clever, freerunning was fun, and the story was captivating.\nPretty good, 8/10", "hours": 1.2, "username": "sm//sh", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
