{"product_id": "201870", "page": 146, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-02", "text": "10/9 for me , one of my favourite games and what to say , I have not finished the single player yet,and i don't know a lot about the story, but i know it looks pretty nice on a Full HD monitor or Tv whatever.\nit has a similar gameplay to Assassin's Creed II and Brotherhood , not the best optimized game though, but it's pretty much playable on a GTX 260 OC edition , 8GB DDR3 Memory and an FX6300 six-core CPU ( I know it's not the best GPU , gonna upgrade it soon)\nI get a Minimum of 35-40 Fps and a Maximum of 50-60 Fps on max settings , excluding AA, i only run it with 2x AA , since i get unplayable framerate drops on 4x and above.\nI'm playing multiplayer mostly and it's fantastic (Y),and in multiplayer i get a solid 60FPS in every situation...\nAll in all I highly recommend, and feel free to add me on Uplay: george940203 or on Steam :)", "hours": 51.0, "user_id": "76561198123298212", "username": "George", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 146, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-31", "text": "I had finished Assassin's Creed 2 and Brotherhood, I like them so much with over a hundred hours of game play.\nThen I started to play Revelations. The begining is ok, an old Ezio, a new city, new assassin friends, a new hook blade, more parkour skills, it sounds good.\nThen I reach the mission \"ON THE DEFENSE\" and I hate this f*** tower defense part of the game with all of my forces. WTF how they put this in the game? It sucks a lot, boring a lot, frustating a lot. If they put it as optional missions, even that I like to do all the missions in the game, it could be ok for me if its possible to skip these f***** parts, but not, it is part of main history, I can't skip this. It sucks a lot.\nI definitively hate this tower defense part of the game, thinking about stop playing and go play other game.", "hours": 4.6, "username": "voomba", "products": 268, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 146, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-29", "text": "the controls with a controller are TERRIBLE!! your character does the\nCOMPLETE OPPISITE OF WHAT YOU TELL IT TO not to mention thegame itself is BUGGY!!!", "hours": 18.4, "user_id": "76561197992556939", "username": "Russell Bluewolf", "products": 76, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-29", "text": "My main problem with this game was the default controls and the fact that Ezio looks way too much like my dad to be an Assassin and the  CONTROLS ARE ABSOLOUTLEY HORRIBLE. everything else is great! the story, the parkour, the open world. it all comes together very nicely. i give it a solid 8/10.", "hours": 22.6, "user_id": "76561198105807846", "username": "Notorious Mr. Tom", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-28", "text": "Playin from AC 1 to revelations.. this is the best AC yet for RPG fanatics like me.. No annoying jumping puzzles or draggy story", "hours": 18.9, "username": "Valorien", "products": 139, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-28", "text": "To me, this game is sumarized in two words. And these two words really don't warrant a spoilers warning (in my opinion) because ultimately the developers were very open in saying that this is what you'd experience when playing this game BEFORE the game came out.\nSo here's the two words. You get to say: \"Goodbye Ezio\". Which. You get to play as him ONE LAST TIME, before inevitably saying goodbye to the most timeless and compelling character in all of Video Game history (my opinion). Though this game DOES wrap up the story arc oriented around The Apple Of Eden, to me, \"Goodbye Ezio\" is the thing that truly stands out.\nThough this game can be sumarized in two words, it's just as amazing as any game in the series (pardoning AC3... what a disapointment).", "hours": 42.7, "user_id": "76561197983915759", "username": "Orphanlast", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-28", "text": "It hasn't the story of AC2 or Brotherhood but the gameplay isn't bad!It's nice to play in your free time", "hours": 7.6, "user_id": "76561198126975247", "username": "SteoX", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-26", "text": "Yet another installment of the Assassin's Creed series; of course, Desmond's story continues after the unexpected ending in Brotherhood and this time he relives the last chapter of Ezio's memories and like Rome in Brotherhood, Constantinople is where all the events take place in this game.\nMost of the features on this game are taken from Brotherhood like the fighting, economy, recruitment, etc. Of course, it has some changes to some of them, but to its core are the same as Brotherhood. One of the highlights about this game is you get to know more about Altair from the first game.\nLike all Assassin's Creed this one is no different about telling a good story. Like the previous AC installment there is a lot of things to along the way like additional missions to the main, etc.\nA good improvement are graphics and how the everything looks (going from the world to the character models); you should be able to find a lot of detail through all the game. As the previous games the music is and it keep being really good and it fits perfectly to what happens.\nA clearly great improvement to this game was the multiplayer which was improve in good ways compared to the previous, which of course introduces new modes to play, which feels fresh in the PVP multiplayer world, not the classic run with your gun and shoot everything moving kinda multiplayer; is all about style and how you eliminate your targets. Lots and lots of rewards, challenges and even more context to the Templars background.\nAlso, if you got the Lost Archives DLC you will be able to know more details about Desmond's story, like what his past was and some other stuff; this may add some context if you want to know more about the characters; I'll say it will be like an hour or hour and a half of extra content.\nBottom line, if you like the Assassin's Creed series, this one will probably be something you like; so, what are you waiting for? get that hidden blade a target and go for it!...", "hours": 43.4, "username": ".: D :.", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-25", "text": "Good game", "hours": 18.6, "username": "DickButt", "products": 20, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-23", "text": "here's what i think..\n.Fistly,\nthis is for the children..\n.if you never like \"books\" or doing your homework for school, because you simply do not like \"mathematics, or social sciences, or history lessons,\" this is boring,,, and you thought playing video games are better,,well you're probabley right... well then,, this is the \"History lesson\" you may not want to miss..This game,,, is a History lesson.\nAfter this you will want to do better in school...This is a family orientated game, a \"Historical game\" where you can learn, love and play,,...\n2NDly: I would recommend this because of it's storyline, Actions, environment, not to mention the hardwork in computer graphics/ designer,  and the type of gameplay temptations you \"aquire\" along your journey.......Great game......", "hours": 1.0, "username": "{ The Seat }", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-22", "text": "I suggest playing 1, 2 and Brotherhood before you play this and definitely all four of them before AC3. Very enjoyable game that's story follows the world of AC quite well! :D", "hours": 9.3, "username": "Zenith", "products": 1170, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-20", "text": "Not as good as any three of the previous games but it's not miles behind. Don't stop playing when they introduce the ridiculous tower defence-esque sequence, it only happens once if you play your cards right. Very strong ending. Buy on sale.", "hours": 8.6, "user_id": "76561198120144294", "username": "obeck521", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 147, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-16", "text": "More of the same.", "hours": 26.2, "username": "kodysandwich", "products": 577, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 148, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-15", "text": "The final Ezio & Altair game and the 2nd best of Ezio's trilogy here is Assassin's Creed Revelations!\nWARNING:Contains Spoilers\nSTORY: You again assume the role of Desmond Miles, after being possessed and killing Lucy, Desmond goes into a coma, he is still inside the animus and meets an individual name Clay, Clay informs Desmond that he must relieve the final memories of Ezio in order to get out and so Desmond does. You now assume Ezio in his early 50's as he heads to Masyaf to find the hidden \"keys\" that will unlock Altair's libary and awaken it's hidden secrets. The templars are also after the keys and after Ezio fights one of the captains and takes a journal that belonged to Niccolo Polo he must head to Constantinople, find the other keys, and stop the templars before they can use the knowledge for their own gains. The story here was honestely the worst for Ezio, he felt like a mentor to the other characters and didn't really put in much of a impact in this game but I understand because this is Ezio's final game and it portray's both his final struggles and his somewhat tiredness towards his own brotherhood.7.1/10\nGRAPHICS: The graphics are the best out of Ezio's trilogy enough said.9.5/10\nGAMEPLAY: The gameplay was way WAY less difficult than AC:B was, you could buy all the stuff without going through some stupid fetch quest for it, the full sync was better, and it only frustrated me once.Simple as that.8/10\nCONCLUSION: This was a fine way to end Ezio & Altair's story but it should've been stronger like AC:B was at least, but Ubisoft still tried their best with gameplay and a hookblade, GO HOOKBLADE!\nBUY RANK:1-2 (Pretty good price so far, you should buy it now or wait till a sale. Your choice.)", "hours": 17.1, "user_id": "76561198028032411", "username": "Claylex", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 148, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-12", "text": "This game WOULD be incredible had it not stopped working on the 2nd mission. Now every time I try to play on story mode, a window pops up that says \"ACRP has stopped working,\" and there is no apparent solution. Graphics, content and gameplay are incredible for when it was made and would be a must buy if not for the issue. 5/10", "hours": 53.0, "user_id": "76561198075565767", "username": "<mr.rob0t>", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 148, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-11", "text": "Drawbacks:\nGraphics haven't improved much from AC2 and Brotherhood. In fact, I noticed that there were a bit more glitches in this game than the previous ones.\nNewcomers to the series will definitely not benefit from starting with this one, but this has been an issue since AC2.\nStory and characters are not as engaging as the first 2 arcs of Ezio's story. And the modern side to the tale gets more convoluted than ever.\nGood points:\nThe setting of Constantinople is again beautifully crafted. Turn off the HUD and explore.\nThe music is gorgeous, shame that this is Jesper Kyd's last work in the Assassin's Creed series.\nThe multiplayer has improved and added new game modes. But you might be hard pressed to find a lobby nowadays.\nThe bomb mechanics are quite nice and the hookblade as well.\nI would recommend this game only if you have liked Ezio and you want a conclusion to his side of the story.", "hours": 58.5, "username": "SpartanQueen", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 148, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-10", "text": "I played AC1 AC Brother hood and this game....For Revelations Im sad to say that I would give this a 3-10...Yes it is a fun game but only until you have burnt threw the story.Once the Story is done..The game quickly turns from a game to a chore as I spent Hours doing nothing but buying everything.the Desmonds Journy back story...yea that was a waste of time as it has you running threw the program in FP mode just traveling around a maze while he explains his lifes story.BORING...I swear other then the main story this game reaks of time waster.Wouldent play it a 2nd time.", "hours": 49.0, "user_id": "76561198062865547", "username": "RazSpirit", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
