{"product_id": "201870", "page": 149, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "Only complaint I have is I feel like the targeting is off here and there. I.e. when attempting to assassinate a cowardly Templar Captain at one of the dens, I always jumped on his GUARD even though I had the CAPTAIN targeted, absolutely dead in my sights. I tried it a few times just to make sure I wasn't crazy. Idk if that's on purpose to force you to chase after the guy and make it more difficult or if it's a bug or w/e, but it was more frustrating than it should've been.\nOverall though I can't NOT enjoy an AC game.", "hours": 34.1, "username": "Eeves", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 149, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "Ok, I like the game but there are MAJOR flaws.\n1) The Aspect ratio is fixed to 16:9 so black bars for us who don't have a 16:9 moniter.\n2) Controls are pretty horrible, they're rebindable but badly IE Run is Left Mouse. Jump is E/Shift. They're just horrible\n3)Parkour is no where near as fun as it is on a console. Buy the game, but for Xbox or Playstation.\nEDIT After playing, it's alright, but still better on Console", "hours": 32.2, "username": "Dirty Dan", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 149, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "Great storyline", "hours": 26.1, "username": "Beidh", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 150, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "Finally! That word could define my impressions of AC Revelations. I finished the AC, AC 2 and AC Brotherhood (Oh my god! What a terrible game!) on my PS3. Definietly, Revelations IS the best AC so far (didn't play AC 3, Liberty or Black Flag yet). The history is by far a way better. Maybe just because explains a lot of things (Oh really?! Revelations, right \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665?!). The game doesn't wait to the right end to show something really cool, like the previous sequels. There are some awesome action moments, like Ezio's jumping obstacles while dodging bullets and pursuing a boat. The ambientation is a way better than Rome (at least for me). And the mechanics... well, ok! They still \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. But I kinda desliked a little less than the previous AC's. Maybe the PC's version is a way better, maybe they really did some improvement. Still, you will continue to climb undesired walls, to jump on undesired ledges and to target undesired people sometimes (a lot of times), but still worth it. The history is freaking cool. It's the first AC's game that I could finished without getting bored and the first that I could finished so quickly. I mean 22 hours in 3 days and a half, not bad for an Assassin's Creed.\nAC1 - 7\nAC2 - 7.5\nAC Brotherhood - 6\nAC Revelations - 8", "hours": 21.6, "user_id": "76561198022867449", "username": "Messo", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 150, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-26", "text": "This game is absolutely fun to play.", "hours": 10.3, "username": "syafiqyahya", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
