{"product_id": "201870", "page": 156, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "Revelations takes the Assassin's Creed formula and cooks it for too long. Boring and frustrating side-quests get shoved in your way, the crafting system is just useless for most stuff and all the things you find fun in AC2 you won't find fun in Revelations.\nThat being said, the new-ish setting is entertaining, and some of the stalking stuff is entertaining, as is having a hook.", "hours": 17.2, "username": "nathan", "products": 606, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 156, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-03", "text": "My favorite of the AC2 era games, it delves into both the end of Altair and Ezio's era in a cool way. The annoying climbing puzzles and tedious tombs of AC:Brotherhood are gone, replaced with more action-oriented 'tomb sequences' that felt inspired by Uncharted 2 that were way more entertaining. Only main annoyance was that there is a bug with the deposit you're supposed to get every 20 minutes that made its frequency vary from 20 minutes to multiple hours, so I felt stiffed on my income for a lot of the game... but the best armor and weapon aren't bought with gold anyway, so it didn't really hurt the experience overall.", "hours": 23.4, "user_id": "76561197970549991", "username": "RedFox", "products": 461, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 157, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-31", "text": "This game was very conclusion to the great trilogy of Ezio Auditore. We followed him from Assassin's Creed II to Assassin's Creed brotherhood to this one. I feel like the game had been a great experience, yet it felt like it was lacking in some sense. The graphics were amazing the story of course still great, but it was a bit short. The game I felt came too soon and they could have added so much more! I did enjoy exploring the cities although it seemed to go too fast to explore, and creating the bombs with different ingredients were a fun trip too. The city of Istanbul is were you are located at and it just beautiful! maybe on of the greatest locations so far. The addition of the knife grappling hook also made it ever more so worth the while.\nI loved it, but wouldn't call it my favirote. Though I would recommend it for any person who has completed the first three.", "hours": 41.6, "username": "Moon", "products": 1234, "early_access": false}
