{"product_id": "201870", "page": 163, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-30", "text": "It's really good because it keeps everything that made Assassin's Creed II and Assassin's Creed Brotherhood great and added new elements to gameplay like the hookshot that allows for faster climbing and ziplines that allow for faster travel around the city.  It also explains the history of Altair and how Desmond, Altair, and Ezio are all connected.  Assassin's Creed Revelations is not a perfect game however.  It's too short with the campaign being only about 10-11 hours.  Also the setting in Constantinople is not as fun and scenic as the Italian cities or Rome, Florence etc.  I still would reccommend it to anyone who's played all the other Assassin's Creed games.  I would give this game a 7.5/10.", "hours": 14.5, "username": "Frozen", "products": 105, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 163, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-30", "text": "It's the perfect closure for Ezio's trilogy; however, it does not offer something completely new and if you were getting tired by Brotherhood's mechanisms, Revelations will definitely not change your mind.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "Rook", "products": 579, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 163, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-30", "text": "I loved it. I would have written a review for the original one since that's the one that got me hooked on the series, but I played that one on the PS3, so I can't review the PC version. Fair enough. I have the PC version now, though, and am planning on playing it.\nRevelations, on the other hand, I played all the way through on the PC version. First off, if you've played this game or any of the others on the consoles only, you have no idea what they're supposed to look like. The graphics are astounding. That out of the way, the obligatory \"eye candy\" factor, what's the game really like?\nThe good: As is the case in every previous installment, you can lose yourself completely in this one. You don't have to, but if you want to spend a month playing nothing but this game, you can. On the other hand, and that's another thing I like, if you just like the story, you don't have to invest the rest of your year in it. And it's a good story too. Great dialogue, color and characters that actually feel real with a few twists thrown in on top. As I like to say when I run into that rare creature, the game with a good story, \"it would make a great movie.\"\nIt ties up a lot of loose ends too, closing out the stories of Altair and Ezio very well indeed and, quite frankly, even as a fan I was beginning to reach the point where I wasn't sure that Ezio's story, as fascinating as it is, could be milked any further. I like closure. At some point. I'm done with Ezio and Altair now, and not in a bad way. It's all good.\nThe bad? The side games get a bit repetitive. At first I was determined to dominate the Med and renovate every public lavatory in Constantinople before I'd finish the game. At the end, not so much. But that's what I like about these games: You can carry on with the side games, quests, mini-games and so on for as long as you like them, and then you can get right back into the story and finish the thing if you've had all you can stand. And you'll STILL end up with weeks of play time. You don't miss out on anything.\nExcept for the Desmond's Journey optional side game, which I only made it through the second sequence of before I tired of it. Placing blocks in space and playing first person Tetris just doesn't do it for me, sorry. But I didn't lose anything because of it, so *shrug*. I would have loved to hear all about Desmond growing up, though, but it just wasn't worth it for me.\nOverall? A great romp. Beautiful, stunning even, with a story that reads like a book to the point where I couldn't wait to go to the next mission point to find out what happened next. Just like a good book. That with some awesome fight animations, controls that keep getting better and cinematics made for movies, not to mention the awesome soundtrack and it's a very nice package of awesome interactive entertainment indeed. Oh, and with a bit of history thrown in for good measure.\nI may be lonely in appreciating the database entries about historic locations and people, but I appreciate them very much. History isn't taught near enough in schools nowadays.\n9 out of 10.", "hours": 28.5, "user_id": "76561197996899190", "username": "MishaTX", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 163, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-29", "text": "Pretty good, yo.", "hours": 18.7, "username": "Jennifer!", "products": 442, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-28", "text": "but why i cant play multyplayer i try but no body is on ;(", "hours": 11.7, "user_id": "76561198044266004", "username": "EgN| Mr.Fantastic", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-28", "text": "Taking the best from the previous series, game gives you an amazing experience, action-packed intense gameplay, random and interesting missions. Story is great, ancient Istanbul is huge and interesting to explore, music is so much epic. Some people say brotherhood/revelations is more like addon, but this isn`t true. It took me almost 30 hours for about 87% total sync and still have some side-missions left.\nIf you`re up for a good mature story in an open-world sandbox - pick it up immediately.\nIf you`re a series fan - this is must have of course, will fill up the missing story chapters so you can see the untold earlier Altair`s stories, Desmond past and so much more.", "hours": 31.3, "user_id": "76561197996393893", "username": "dizz", "products": 1091, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-28", "text": "This game follows the formula established in AC2 and AC:Brotherhood.  You'll find the same economy system, shop restorations, etc.  The notable additions are:\n* Extended activities to do once your assassin recruits level up\n* Craftable Bombs\n* Assassin building defense minigame (essentially tower defense)\nThe tower defense minigame is a bit annoying, but I'm glad they introduced it since in Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood, there weren't any serious consequenses for allowing your notariety to max out (by doing \"illegal\" things).\nIf you haven't played either of the prequals, hold off on playing this one, since the story picks up where they left off.  I don't think that the first Assassin's Creed game is necessary, however, to know what's going on.\nI enjoyed AC2 and AC:Brotherhood and I enjoyed AC:Revelations as well.  They stuck to what worked in the previous games and added a bit more.  I'm glad I didn't get it when it was full priced but I think anything around $10 is easy to justify for this title.\nEDIT: I noticed, as I was recently playing, that I really like the NPC models/textures.  They are significantly more alive and colorful that they have been in the past AC games.  Quite impressed.", "hours": 71.6, "username": "RagingRoosevelt", "products": 474, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "All Assassin's Creeds are legen . . . . wait for it . . . . dary. LEGENDARY", "hours": 106.3, "username": "GKASIOS", "products": 731, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "Favorite AC game up to III.", "hours": 12.0, "username": "RocketPool", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "It's kind of impossible to follow all the Assassin's Creed yearly releases, so I'm still 2 games behind. Although this is inferior to Brotherhood I did enjoy Revelations more, maybe because I was a bit tired of Assassin's Creed when I played the previous one. I enjoyed Constantinopla and Ezio's final chapter, he is truly one of the best protagonists of this generation and AC story is more enjoyable if we see it as Ezio's personal journey. All the crap around Animus, Desmond and the gods is a big, giant mess.\n3,5/ 5", "hours": 13.1, "username": "Berto", "products": 567, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed Revelations is one of the weakest points in the series, but it doesn't mean it's bad, the game just mostly focuses on story instead of gameplay. It is about the final days of our assassin's Ezio and Altair. This game kinda made me feel old and experienced just like Ezio after climbing the same tower in the same generic city and fighting the same guards with the same strategies.\nPros:\n+Hook blade\n+Assassins Guild got improved with a personal story for each assassin\n+Tower defence minigame to protect you'r guild headquarters\n+Economic got some balancing\n+Experimenting with ingredients to create bombs\n+Story focused on two main characters Altair and Ezio, also reveals a few things about Desmond\n+Multiplayer continues to improve with a story element\n+Nostalgic moments\n+Tons of revelations\n+1st person puzzles\nCons:\n-Same combat system\n-Generic and not memorable city\n-Feels like a story filler\nScore:\n8/10", "hours": 33.6, "username": "Scyrenus", "products": 1934, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "thumbs up", "hours": 61.6, "username": "lanza del relampago", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Marking the end of Ezio's journey as a Master assassin, this game is kind of end of an era for many AC gamers i guess.\nEzio saga- AC2, AC Brotherhood and ACR.\nMP servers-dead.", "hours": 42.5, "username": "Chetshire", "products": 141, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 164, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "It is definitly one of the must play games. I had blast with it so far and I think others that get it and play it will have a blast as well.", "hours": 11.2, "username": "Gooey Oso", "products": 282, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "It's Assassin's Creed. Best of the Ezio trilogy.\n10/10", "hours": 24.4, "username": "Socki the Sock", "products": 1544, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "very good", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561198005055481", "username": "Asmod", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Another AC2 expansion pack played. The story didn't move an inch, no horses, no controlling Desmond in the real world and no explanation why we are in some hippie wet dream. On the other hand, the city and the missions themselves are quite enjoyable. If they want to end this story in a bang they better be making AC3 for some time now, or it's another ruined franchise. A little padding and feature creep is not the end of the world(pun intended), but it's a fine line to tread.", "hours": 39.6, "username": "somini", "products": 469, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "In all honesty an insult to Assassin's Creed.\nRevelations trades the excellent story-telling and character development in Assassin's Creed 2 as well as the improvements in gameplay in Assassin's Creed Brotherhood for meaningless item collection and achievement hunting.\nAvoid.", "hours": 11.0, "username": "Jeremy", "products": 188, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "Very good game. Best one of the assassins.", "hours": 145.9, "username": "crisgrossi", "products": 1068, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "Probably the weakest of the franchise but a satisfying end of the Ezio/Altair story.\n7/10", "hours": 8.6, "username": "Ashes.", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-11", "text": "Really good I recoemend it.", "hours": 18.1, "username": "Rain", "products": 240, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-08", "text": "Assassin's Creed Revelations is a great addition to the ever expanding and intriguing Assassin Creed series. At first look and play the game seems as usual and repetitive as the others. Revelations continues off with Ezio Auditore an assassin fighting to rebuild his brotherhood while trying to piece together some of the past history of the Assassin Brotherhood. On top of that he sparks up somewhat a romance with another main character.  All in all the game deliver a very immersive gameplay, expanded its resources, and even added new locations. Although not the most gripping AC game so far it earned a place in the story by shedding more light on past events and developing Desomond Miles character for the future series.", "hours": 39.7, "user_id": "76561198010617834", "username": ":(){ :|: & };:", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-04", "text": "The final installment of Ezio's story.  Ezio is now an old man but still an active assassin.  The introduction of the hook blade is one of the big changes in this game, allowing for more options in both fighting and freerunning.  One thing I really liked is the hook-and-run, which allowed you to get past a bunch of guards making a roadblock.  This game also introduced the den defense minigame, which I wasn't very fond of.  I want to freerun and assassinate people, not play a tower-defense game...  One more thing they added was bomb crafting, which I never used ever...  While not as good as the first two, Assassin's Creed Revelations is worth playing simply because it provides closure to Ezio's story.", "hours": 31.2, "username": "[\u2665] OMFGeoff", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 165, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-02", "text": "Jogabilidade muito  boa.", "hours": 58.9, "username": "Cybercalango", "products": 365, "early_access": false}
