{"product_id": "201870", "page": 167, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-07", "text": "Another great AC title, gameplay stays basically the same from the previous two titles. It started kind of slow storywise but it surely picked up halfway through the game. Devs added a \"tower defense\" mini mode within the game, it's mostly optional quests though. Story is basically about revelations, and gotta say the ending was very \"revealing\". Think a combination of films Wanted (Assassins) and Knowing (The revelation within the game). Very intense.", "hours": 10.0, "username": "R4DFIELD", "products": 417, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 167, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-06", "text": "I liked it a lot. Don't understand why this game got so much hate - to me it was just as good as Brotherhood, if not better. Storyline is exciting, location is alright, graphics are great. Multiplayer needs more players but is a lot of fun. Only issue is optimization - at one point I had to disable 3 CPU threads to get past a checkpoint (game crashed otherwise)", "hours": 10.1, "username": "rush b blyat", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
