{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-25", "text": "Revelations is the Fourth Installment of the Assassin's Creed series.\nIn Revelations, you pick up a bit afterwards where Brotherhood left off.\nIf you haven't played Brotherhood, beware of the lines below.\nYou've been warned.\nSince Ezio now has no enemies in Rome, and his Brotherhood keeps expanding, he  decided to learn more about the Assassin's, and the best way to do it, would be to visit their birthplace, the Assassin Den of Masyaf.\nThis is the last game that was played on the skin of Ezio Auditore da Firenze, in this game, he already has quite some age. It would be impossible for him to live much more afterwards. This game is the one that concludes *his* story.\nI have to say, the game was okay to me. Some people may not like it.\nIt's set in Constantinople, wich is one of the largest cities that ever existed.\nYou've got alot of collectibles to find, and the story itself is great.\nYou also have Multiplayer, wich is okay, but too focused on upon.\nI'd say, good purchase, but get it on discount. Not on a full price.", "hours": 69.9, "username": "TwistedRaven", "products": 538, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-18", "text": "Worth it for the multiplayer, if you like The Ship. Singleplayer you ask? Never touch the stuff.", "hours": 8.4, "username": "ingves", "products": 1963, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-18", "text": "My least favorite of the Ezio trilogy, but just barely. Still a fun experience and a solid conclusion to Ezio and Altair's stories.", "hours": 53.8, "username": "Sique", "products": 62, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-14", "text": "A worthy end to Ezio (and i guess Altair's) story. It falls just short of AC Brotherhood and ranks with ACII firmly in second place. Really not sure how they could have gone from gems such as this to the mediocrity that is AC3 though.", "hours": 28.3, "user_id": "76561197970329460", "username": "Aeneas2020", "products": 542, "early_access": false}
