{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-10", "text": "all i can say is buy this on sale it dont have mutch game play in it took me like 19h start to finish but that is because i have played them all and i am pritty good at the game. never played the multiplayer side to thes games but i would think they are good.", "hours": 19.8, "user_id": "76561198010540441", "username": "Metalsage", "products": 342, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-07", "text": "These games are all the same, so my recommendations will all be the same.\nThe world we get to assassin in are quite nice and great at representing these ancient cityscapes. That said, the storyline is bad in every game, and the games try their best to make them as historically inacurate as possible. PC port is terrible - fair at best. Just don't buy them.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Graeme", "products": 1044, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 171, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-07", "text": "Not the best of the series to be honest, however makes use of similar mechanics from AC:Brotherhood. Quite easy overall but has port problems causing crashes and  wierd glitches.\nIf you do come accross any crashes (Occurs on i5/i7 CPUs) set the game's affinity to just one CPU and play to the end of the memory sequence and then switch back.", "hours": 18.0, "username": "NyHoK", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 172, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-06", "text": "After the collapse of Cesare Borgia on Rome,Ezio seeks for answers to questions that were following him for a very long time during his lifetime.As a result,he left Rome and headed to Masyaf,the home of the first appeared Assassins,but after so many centuries since the Crusades,Masyaf hasn't been home to the Assassins for a very long time.As he explores Masyaf,he heads to Constantinople,since the Templars who were on Masyaf where sent by their Masters from Constantinople. About the gameplay ; Graphics are increased and are even better,Ezio is more lethal and wise in combat than ever,allowing you to defeat any kind of enemies even with the worst weapon.", "hours": 213.2, "username": "DRMZZY", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 172, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-02", "text": "IMO the best part in the Ezio Auditore trilogy, in fact, this is the best game in the whole AC series until now (AC3), watch the Assassins Creed: Embers movie after you've finished AC:R, tears will follow.", "hours": 33.3, "username": "Cobra", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 172, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-05-02", "text": "Single player story sucks...Lorewise doesn't really make any sense as you team up with opressors against the rebels! Huh? What's wrong with Ubi?Too much praise to Ottomans as if they were  the best civilizations of all time...Yeah you read right! Suleiman is depicted as a good bloke too...yeah right :P... I recommend it only for multiplayer which is fun...So 4/10", "hours": 133.2, "username": "Christos", "products": 427, "early_access": false}
