{"product_id": "201870", "page": 172, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-01", "text": "As the third and final installment in the trilogy, this is by far the best out of the three. Ezio, 25 years later, finally completes his lifelong mission, with all the best things from II and Brotherhood combined in addition to a new romance, a much deeper storyline and more enemies/weapons, this is definitely a game you'd want to play til the end.", "hours": 34.2, "username": "Maverick", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 172, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-27", "text": "If you liked Brotherhood then you'd also like this game. It's very similar to brotherhood only the city is not as big as its easier to use your fellow assassins. I thought the storyline was more interesting then brotherhood though the game felt like it was shorter. Still, if you are playing through the series then make sure to stop and play this game!", "hours": 32.8, "user_id": "76561198002986817", "username": "Phantom Virus", "products": 356, "early_access": false}
