{"product_id": "201870", "page": 175, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-29", "text": "It's alright, but taken as a whole, it's probably my least favorite Assassin's Creed game so far (AC:III or portables not included). It suffers from feature creep - bombs seem like a silly improvement that will get little use, and the tower defense minigame is straight up dumb. The freerunning is the same as before, with no real changes. The meta-story with Desmond is a nonstarter, fleshing out his backstory a tiny bit but not resolving the cliffhanger of AC:Brotherhood at all.\nOverall recommendation: it's more of the same from the last games, except not quite as well executed. Give it a whirl if it's on sale.", "hours": 23.1, "user_id": "76561197988746017", "username": "/ArcHammer*", "products": 300, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 175, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-29", "text": "Revelations take the series to the next level adding more combat moves and special objectives. Hours can be lost in seconds playing this game, love it.", "hours": 9.9, "user_id": "76561198009362163", "username": "Wild-Card", "products": 239, "early_access": false}
