{"product_id": "201870", "page": 177, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-24", "text": "GUH...well holy\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 talk about revelations. That ending was intense. It really is just a bigger, better continuation of the series. Not quite perfect because of the combat system and stuff, but everything else is so fantastic that it pretty much overrides it. And the story is so damn good! Jesus now I'm excited for AC3...9.75/10", "hours": 7.4, "username": "-=TheDoctor=-", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 177, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-23", "text": "<3", "hours": 60.9, "username": "Kenka Banch\u014d 6: Soul & Blood", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 177, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-19", "text": "The game finally speeds up the pace which was slowed down in Brotherhood and rushes through diverse set of events without ever leaving the space for boredom. It feels somewhat shorter than its predecessor, but this helps keeping things interesting through and through. Gone are the brilliant puzzles from ACII and Brotherhood, but they're replaced by first-person storytelling sequences with platforming elements. Main theme by Lorne Balfe performed by the winner of a fan singing contest sounds amazing and is probably the most memorable musical piece in the whole series to date. Multiplayer got a facelift as well and now features a sort of a storyline with cutscenes. The game once again manages to pull off a mind-blowing and heartfelt ending that leaves you with a melancholic afterthought.\nThe best AC game since ACII, a magnificent conclusion to the stories of two brilliant characters.", "hours": 113.0, "username": "Toff", "products": 3154, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 177, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-14", "text": "Revelations feels like a true progression to the Assassin's Creed franchise, expanding on everything that was new in brotherhood, but giving it purpouse and depth. Assassin recruits are given more meaning, as once you level them to 10, you can assign them to a den and begin a mission with them in which you actuall interact with your recruits. Gaining recruits seems some similarly unique missions, as aposed to the simple 'defend the civilian' from Brotherhood, which still exists but in lesser numbers. Missions for your rEcruits also has a purpose, letting you gain control of other reagions of the world while you work towards your goals in Constantinople.\nThe story is much richer in Revelations, and ties up loose ends, and gives a very satisfying conclusion to both Ezio and Altair's storylines. Desmonds story is progressed only slightly, but some of his backstory is filled in, more than him actually making any forward progression in the over arching plot.\nThe new setting is refreshing from ACII and Brotherhood's focus on Italy, and the new characters you meet are easier to connect with, and care about than in previous titles.\nThe new hookblade adds some much needed precision and functionality to free-running, and adds some speed to vertical transitions. Finishing animations add a lot to combat, and might actually make you stick around and fight a pack of guards instead of running away and hidding.\nAll in all, this s the best game in the Ezio trillogy, and in the first 4 games.", "hours": 18.0, "username": "Bloodstorm", "products": 522, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 177, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-13", "text": "\u041d\u0443 \u0432\u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0437\u0431\u0438\u0441\u044c", "hours": 53.5, "username": "batya", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 178, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-11", "text": "The end of Ezio's stab-and-jump adventures.\nWhile still a very polished game, it's definitely the weakest of the AC2 series. The base game itself is fine, but bomb crafting is annoying, horse carriage driving is utterly stupid and the Tower Defense game is really bad (except for the tutorial mission, you can avoid playing it).\nThe good parts are a fun assassin meta game, almost no current world scenes and a beautiful city to run around in.\nOnly play this if you can't get enough of Aassassin's Creed and Ezio after finishing AC2 and Brotherhood.", "hours": 49.6, "username": "Fart of Presto", "products": 4802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 178, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-11", "text": "Acabei de terminar, o que dizer de AC.... Melhor s\u00e9rie? Melhor jogo? Melhor tudo? N\u00e3o sei, s\u00f3 sei dizer que manteve a qualidade dos anteriores, um jogo supremo em tudo....aguardando apenas jogar o AC 3 que ouvi dizer que \u00e9 o melhor de todos, s\u00f3 fico imaginando.\nAmigos, podem comprar qualquer jogo da s\u00e9rie AC, n\u00e3o v\u00e3o se arrepender...", "hours": 76.5, "username": "bubsylopez\u00ae", "products": 786, "early_access": false}
