{"product_id": "201870", "page": 178, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-07", "text": "Al\u00e9m da mudan\u00e7a de cen\u00e1rio e as \u00f3bvias adi\u00e7\u00f5es na hist\u00f3ria, n\u00e3o espere nada muito novo em AC Revelations. Basicamente os mesmos recursos que apareceram no AC Brotherhood foram mantidos (quase) intactos aqui. As granadas talvez tenham sido a adi\u00e7\u00e3o mais not\u00e1vel, mas s\u00e3o praticamente in\u00fateis se voc\u00ea j\u00e1 est\u00e1 acostumado com a jogabilidade da s\u00e9rie. A hist\u00f3ria, como sempre, come\u00e7a lenta e previs\u00edvel e segue assim at\u00e9 a metade. \u00c9 s\u00f3 da\u00ed pra frente que a coisa fica realmente ~REVELADORA~, com um dos finais mais jaw-dropping que eu j\u00e1 vi.", "hours": 25.9, "username": "tiotuli", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 178, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-07", "text": "Really good game. I can't really comment on any part of the side mission or anything about the game other then the main story as it is the only thing I did. It was by far the best in terms of story and gameplay.", "username": "SQUENIX BASED REMAKE", "products": 2092, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 178, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-11-02", "text": "See my previous Assassin's Creed reccomendations.  Combat is boring less bosses (targets) than previous iterations, bosses are no different than normal soldiers, many pointless sidequests, more options but no real reason to use one over another.  Less interesting dungeon zones in this one, some minor perks to doing challenges, but really this game is no different than any of the previous games, mechanics wise.  Climbing is less frustrating but that's just polish of the mechanic present in the last three games.\nThe story was never all that amazing in these games, and this one reveals essentially nothing towards the overall arching story in the name of making more sequels.  Overall, pretty much nothing interesting happened here and everything was forgettable.  Considering its supposed to be the end of Ezio's story, they could've done better  Again, welcome to sequels.\nMultiplayer is enjoyable with some caveats, but it will probably die now that AC3 has been released.  C'est la vie.", "hours": 166.7, "username": "I'm Not Sue", "products": 603, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 178, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-02", "text": "Ezio likes turtles.", "hours": 29.6, "username": "the dude abides", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-02", "text": "\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0445\u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e. \u0418\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0433\u043b\u044f\u0434\u0438\u0442 \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e,\u044f \u0441\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0430\u044e \u0435\u0451 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0435\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u043e\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438. \u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0435 \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0432 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0435 \u0436\u0434\u0430\u043b \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0434\u0435\u044f\u043b\u0441\u044f,\u0447\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430\u043c \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0435 \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0447\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b \u0443\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044f\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044e \u0410\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0438\u0440\u0430,\u043d\u043e \u043c\u044b \u0435\u0433\u043e \u0432\u0438\u0434\u0438\u043c \u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u043e 6 \u0440\u0430\u0437,\u0447\u0442\u043e \u043e\u0447\u0435\u043d\u044c \u043e\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0442. \u0427\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u043e \u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u044f,\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043b \u0442\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043a\u043e \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u0433\u043e,\u0447\u0442\u043e\u0431\u044b \u0443\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0442\u044c,\u0447\u0435\u043c \u0432\u0441\u0451 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0441\u044c \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0410\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0438\u0440\u0430,\u0438\u0431\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0431\u044b\u043b\u0430 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0435\u0439.\n\u041d\u0430\u0434\u0435\u044e\u0441\u044c,\u0447\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e \u0410\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0438 \u0441\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435.\n10/10.", "hours": 35.8, "username": "BLACK JACKASS", "products": 465, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-01", "text": "\u0418\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u0445\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0448\u0430,\u043d\u043e \u0435\u0441\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u0444\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442 assassins creed,\u0442\u043e \u0432\u044b \u043d\u0435 \u043e\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0443\u044e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b-\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043f\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0447\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u042d\u0446\u0438\u043e \u0410\u0443\u0434\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0435 \u0414\u0430 \u0424\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0446\u0435.\u041d\u0443 \u0430 \u0435\u0441\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u044b \u0444\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442 \u0442\u043e \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e \u0433\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0443+ \u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0435\u0440 \u043e\u0447\u0435\u043d\u044c \u043e\u0440\u0438\u0433\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0435 \u0441\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0451\u043d btotherhood.\u0412\u044b\u0432\u043e\u0434-\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\n9/10", "hours": 3.6, "username": "Skynej", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-31", "text": "A very good game from a very good story line. I have been a fan of AC for a long time. I even liked the 1st game to much of everyone's surprise. But this is a must play to see what has happened after brotherhood. The mechanics are similar, but you can do tower defense too (but I didn't do more than one. I kept my meter to secret.) Overal a good game, great characters, a twist at the end, and 30+ hours of gameplay. Go and buy it before AC3 comes out.", "hours": 28.4, "username": "RandomCapture", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-31", "text": "A lot will feel familiar for veterans of the AC series, but the game MORE THAN MAKES up for this familiarity by bumping the story up another notch. PLAY PLAY PLAY", "username": "Tabulation", "products": 467, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-30", "text": "A step back in playability that adds a plethora of new mechanics, has boring, immersion-breaking (but optional) tutorials, and then gives you little chance to experiement with the few combinations that are consistently successful. Good for the last twenty minutes as Sixteen and Desmond carry an otherwise lackluster plot continuation.", "hours": 23.3, "user_id": "76561197974173032", "username": "Zeral", "products": 271, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-30", "text": "Guidos In Constantinople and\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665Cray.", "hours": 24.2, "user_id": "76561197977328933", "username": "Indoorsman", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-30", "text": "Overall they've done a great job continuing to improve the mechanics from game to game. This one is streamlined in a good way and has done away with the horse riding between cities, etc. You get in the action and stay there. The Desmond chapters have more in common with Portal, but If you liked Brotherhood you'll like this one just as much.", "hours": 69.1, "username": "Fogg", "products": 459, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-23", "text": "I have been playing the franchise since it started. I have loved it and I feel this game continues the same gaming mechanics to a strong enough extent. It still carries some of the past glitches, but overall is fun and pretty much exactly what I was expecting.", "hours": 33.6, "username": "\u2764 The Lust of Ass \u2764", "products": 938, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-23", "text": "Playing this game made me realize how much I actually hate the Assassins Creed franchise.", "user_id": "76561198009046516", "username": "DeepEnd", "products": 387, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 179, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-17", "text": "AC II > AC:B > AC:R", "hours": 12.4, "username": "Darkstar", "products": 3280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-17", "text": "Desmond Miles is your typical eighteen year old guy. He works at a bar selling cocktails named after secret societies and carries a blade under each arm. To afford such a lifestyle, he agrees quickly to the ToS of some big-name company and ends up captive in their massive cross-shaped facility and informed that Christianity is not only a lie, muslims are going to kill everyone for their own good. To cover for this fault in logic, Desmond is then informed that nothing is true, everything is permitted, and then is flipped off and winked at by the nurse, who Desmond then kills. No answers are given for this course of events, and the creature \"Q\" from Star Trek is encountered next inside a miniture Tron island, where you're told to purchase the DLC. Meanwhile, there's a minigame involving Desmond's crazy uncle who runs across rooftops and stabs people while throwing money at courtesans which explains why he's everyones great uncle.", "hours": 12.2, "username": "Styke", "products": 1888, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-15", "text": "The single player is fun and addictive, but the multiplayer leaves much to be desired on multiple aspects. I played all the way through the single player without hesitation and had alot of fun doing it, but I quit the online play after a week. If you are into the Creed series or stealth oriented games, the single player mode is well worth the money.", "hours": 26.0, "username": "Frumious Bandersnatch", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-06", "text": "", "hours": 30.8, "username": "1HundredEyes", "products": 255, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-04", "text": "Whereas the previous titles, \"Assassin's Creed II\" and \"Brotherhood\", clearly added gameplay elements and more substance to the franchise, \"Revelations\" more or less follows the preset footsteps of it's predecessors. In addition to a new city, Constantinople, there are some minor additions, most notably the hookblade, the den protection minigame and the assassin training and recruitment episodes have also been upgraded to better fit the context, but as for the technical part, Revelations seems almost stagnated. On the other hand, it all still works so darn well and Revelations is a very beautiful and captivating game. In a sense, it's about the end of an era and a character we've come to love since ACII, which is apparent in the physically aging Ezio Auditore and the conculsion of the Altair chronicles. That is why I strongly recommend you play Revelations, especially if you've already played through the previous games.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "[LUC] Chride", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-26", "text": "AC: Revelations is more of the same. Thankfully the same is still pretty damn good, but it's about time they change things up a bit with AC III.", "hours": 37.7, "username": "facls", "products": 663, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-22", "text": "\u041a\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0442,\u0442\u043e\u0442 \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u044c \u0437\u0440\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0436\u0438\u043b!!!!", "hours": 20.7, "user_id": "76561198062455435", "username": "Vega", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-15", "text": "The Ezio Auditore saga come to a grand conclusion, and does not forget to stop to say hi to Altair and Desmons on it's way.\nlike the ones that came before, this game is great ! you will not be disappointed !", "hours": 52.8, "username": "Exolite", "products": 121, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-06", "text": "Who doesn't like assassin's creed? =)", "hours": 38.8, "user_id": "76561198028477747", "username": "Xiad", "products": 235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-01", "text": "The Good :\n+ Badass Hook Blade\n+ Altaiir Memories are a blast\n+ Loads of variety of bombs\n+ Improved interface\n+ One of the best endings evar! (Though story is not completed)\n+ Assassin's missions are cool\nThe Bad :\n- Counter kills can be wierd sometimes\n- Looks same as it's predecessor's\n- Major bugs in Memory missions", "hours": 26.3, "username": "Watch_Doge", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 180, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-27", "text": "Best franchise i've ever played 10 out of 10", "hours": 51.0, "username": "Ugandan Bruce Lee", "products": 362, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-19", "text": "Muito bom... A AI esta mehlorada e reage conforme suas a\u00e7\u00f5es", "hours": 27.4, "user_id": "76561198026819121", "username": "Eddie_Mad", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-19", "text": "The supposed end of Ezio's story.... while it didn't end with a bang, it did end well. Loved the continuing story arc. Each game gets better and better.", "hours": 72.9, "username": "BLATSPLAT", "products": 917, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-18", "text": "While this game is the 4th main game in the Assassin's Creed universe, it doesn't hold up to the previous 2. Even though Ubisoft managed to keep the great gameplay while adding new components, the story just fell short (in length and in quality).\nDon't get me wrong though, the game is great and worth a play at least once. I was just disappointed that revelations couldve been much better.\nThe multiplayer gets a facelift, keeping the fun-factor going. It's mostly the same, with a few added and new mechanics.\nI got the game at a discount, and was very satisfied with my purchase. If you're following the Assassin's Creed storyline, it wouldn't hurt to pick this up. Don't expect any miracles from the story, though.", "hours": 53.0, "username": "Mr. Roboto", "products": 2488, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-16", "text": "The ending of these games create more questions than answers!", "hours": 30.4, "username": "Bya", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-16", "text": "Follows the same formula as the previous AC2 and Brotherhood titles, however still feels like it's not bringing much to the table as far as Story goes. It was a needless toss in to the second game's storyline I feel like. The addition of the Bombs and the Hook Blade felt weak and unnecessary. Pick it up for 7$ if you really like the series on the next Steam sale, but that's about it. Graphics and Gameplay were fine though.", "hours": 7.3, "username": "Kahran Ramsus", "products": 847, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-08-13", "text": "This game was as good as Brotherhood! Oh... wait... it's the same thing.\\\nIn all seriousness, it wasn't terrible. I give all assassins creed games a fair shot because I absolutely love the story and the game. But this one did feel like it was ripping off the first two and the story wasn't engaging for me. There's lots of new side content which is pretty interesting, but if you wanted to skip to #3 then you wouldn't be missing a ton.", "hours": 13.0, "username": "Nickslice", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-08-05", "text": "Totally love/hate relationship with this game and the series: Plenty of great environments, memorable characters and reasonably good storytelling, thrown in with some of the crappiest controls and laziest game design from a triple A franchise.", "hours": 22.9, "user_id": "76561197964176686", "username": "Don Newman", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-05", "text": "I love the writing in this franchise and the way they finished with the stories of both Ezio and Altair only furthers my appreciation. Just like Brotherhood there is a new big city, new characters and new features with around 20-30 hours single player game time not including all the fun side missions and 100% synchronization challenges. Multiplayer still feels unique and is still going strong with a few upgrades implemented although they still need a text chat, perk balance and lighting that hits the thick players running around on rooftops. If you've played the other AC games you know what to expect by now and if you haven't then go buy the first Assassin's Creed because Revelations feels like a season finale.", "hours": 45.8, "username": "Rivent", "products": 804, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-05", "text": "Oh\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 the old man got really \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing old and now he has to find out about another old man! By the way, the illuminati want to kill you, so you had better kill them before they can kill you or else they will kill your friend.\nYou get these cool frisbee discs that the old man doesn't even throw cause it's olden times and he's dumb like that, not like us cool kids today with hardcore gamesz. Anyway, he looks at the frisbee like an idiot and he is told \"This old guy was really \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing old and look, now he's dead! Holy\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\" and the old man get really scared and kills a guy accidentally.\nThen this guy from the future looks back on this all and he says \"I know what must be done,\" and he calls an AC130 on the scrubs and blows them all away! God bless America.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "State", "products": 461, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 181, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-04", "text": "I love the entire Assassin's Creed line and this one is no exception.  Gameplay is almost identical to the previous titles...that is good and a little bad.  Hopefully they will change it up a bit with the upcoming Assassin's Creed 3 so it doesn't get too stale.", "hours": 66.9, "user_id": "76561197964248370", "username": "SkidCooly", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-31", "text": "its a epic game ........................", "hours": 27.5, "user_id": "76561198066780951", "username": "drinkah", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-28", "text": "This is my first Assassin's creed game,the first play was very interesting,but there had some disadvantage of this game : the storyline is too short!\nI try to finish the game with 100% complete, and it cost me only 50 hours, the game is lack of content, the storyline is very short and the secret extras (like new assassin suit or weapons) was too easy to unlock.\nThe Assassin's creed Revelations still a good game, but not that perfect, I am enjoying in the mutiple player games, the mutiple player is better than single player, more fun and exciting.\nWhatever, I guess I will buy the Assassin's creed 1 and Assassin's creed 2 and brotherhood when speical sale coming, I want to know the full story of Ezio and Altair.", "hours": 57.3, "username": "Reimu Maga", "products": 2990, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-28", "text": "I've had terrible problems with this game that I blame on Ubisoft's online DRM.  Initially I couldn't play the game for a week because I couldn't get the launcher to work.  Eventually I got it working and it was fun for a while.\nNow after 20+ hours of gameplay, the game crashed no problem usually right, just load the latest save point.  Not this time... the game doesn't see any of my save files anymore.  It just offers to create a new game when I try to start single player.  I've tried restoring the files from a backup to no avail.  Ubisoft's online save sync service doesn't seem to do anything either; it makes no difference if I turn it on or off still can't find my saves.\nFor this (and all Ubi games), make sure you turn off their save-sync system.", "hours": 20.9, "username": "Nick", "products": 930, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-27", "text": "Never finish this game, it has the longest unskippable and must..watch to be able to keep playing- credits in any game I have ever played.", "hours": 19.6, "user_id": "76561197970623713", "username": "Pact", "products": 331, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-27", "text": "\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044b\u0439,\u043d\u0430\u043f\u0440\u044f\u0436\u0451\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0435\u0440:)", "hours": 41.5, "user_id": "76561198019516183", "username": "Fear", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-25", "text": "Easily the weakest game in the series. Too many gameplay elements are forced in that have no place in AC. This results in a very long and tedious tutorial and a very easy game.\nEven during puzzles and forced action sequenses the camera points out exactly where to go. For a \"puzzle\" I spend some time figuring out how to go about crossing the room, but it turned out all I have to do is hold free run + W and watch. Don't try deviating from your pre-aproved path, free running, but not free.\nThe story is generaly weak or at some points just downright stupid, the only redeeming part is is a good ending. If you're willing to do annoying first person platforming there's more backstory to discover but I simply found the platforming way too annoying, partly due to the terrible controls and no way to change them.\nThe game is still reasonable in the end but mainly due to being based on AC2, it only substracts from that base.\nIf you are a fan of the series you'll likely pick this up at a sale anyway, but for newcomers to the series this would be a very bad introduction: get AC2 instead.", "hours": 20.3, "username": "Hunter NL", "products": 300, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-25", "text": "Muss sich ein Spiel immer wieder neu erfinden, um Spa\u00df zu machen? Nein, denn auch sp\u00fcrbare Tradition kann sehr gut unterhalten. Revelations zeigt, dass nicht nur gro\u00dfe Innovationen, sondern auch kleine \u00c4nderungen vollkommen ausreichen k\u00f6nnen, um zu fesseln. Man dem Ende der Ezio-Trilogie vorwerfen, dass es mit Ausnahme der zu selten erforderlichen Bomben oder der Den Defense inhaltlich zu wenig Neues geboten wird. Doch das Abenteuer wirkt spielerisch noch runder und hinsichtlicher der Story reifer, weshalb man Ubisoft diese Stagnation nicht \u00fcbel nehmen kann. Zum anderen ist Revelations f\u00fcr mich das erz\u00e4hlerisch bislang st\u00e4rkste AC. Der Multiplayer ist auch sehr gut.", "hours": 17.4, "username": "AndypwnZ", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-23", "text": "Great game. Great series. The last chapter of Ezio is one you don't want to miss. Been a joy playing through this series. I hope they can keep the ball rolling.", "hours": 54.5, "username": "Makaveli", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 182, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "Following AC: Brotherhood and the AC2 was always going to be tough, and despite some fun stuff, the storyline, characters and generic cinema-esque awesomeness of the game, this game seems a little weak to me. It is definitely a transition to another sequel, and I can admit, it's a shame to see Ezio go.", "hours": 35.2, "username": "MagikalKraker", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
