{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-15", "text": "If you've played the other Two (Practically Three) Then you must conclude the story with this final chapter in Ezio's life.\nIt may be short, but its to the Point and you even get to find out something radically that's been hinted at a lot during the first Assasin's Creed.\nCan't wait for the Next Installment...", "hours": 11.1, "username": "Darkus Canning", "products": 418, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Actually quite a good game. the controls are flawless, combat isnt frustrating anymore, seeing as Ezio can kill people easily instead of mashing the attack button for what seems like ages. Very balanced gameplay wise, graphics are nice, and the actual story is fun.", "hours": 18.1, "username": "nightmare", "products": 213, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Straight to the point. 7.5/10. It's Assassin's Creed, if you liked the others, you'll probably like this one. Which is both great and what's bad about this series. The game hasn't really changed the forumla much at all throughout the games, it just feels lazy to me. The game is still fun, it's basically just the same thing as Call of Duty at a lesser extent at this point. I don't really know what else to say about it. It's worth it if you're a fan of the genre/series, but in my opinion it's somewhat boring if you've been playing every single AC game since. Only major complaints are the PC controls are really odd at first, and the graphics are fairly ugly.", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Church of Blow", "products": 942, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "For me this game falls in between Brotherhood and II, leaning more closely to II.  Knocks against it: they've changed the controls ever so slighttly between this one and the last two games; just enough that you'll die a couple of times in the heat of the moment because you fell back into old habits.  The writing is poor; the first assassination made me wonder if the writeres even understood Ezio's character.  New character models for Desmond and Ezio; can't reaally figure out why Ubi decided to do this for the last game in the series, but by they time you start to get used to it, the game is over.  The mini-games suck; I dont' care about a crappy tower defense, or a bomb-making game.\nThings it does right: parkour, and killing.  Luckily, those two things are enough to make it worth it.", "hours": 20.7, "username": "Stunt Rush", "products": 735, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "The best one of its series, very interesting storyline and improved gameplay. However, if you didn't like any of previous games you won't like this one either.", "hours": 51.3, "username": "SlowpokeFarm", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Scumbag me, buying all the collector's edition's and then buying them again on steam store...", "hours": 1.5, "username": "Mit dem K\u00f6rpergr\u00f6\u00dfensong hast", "products": 950, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Em toda vida sempre queremos ou devemos retomar o passado para encontrarmos nossa resposta, este jogo fala muito disso, sugiro joga-lo e entenda do que um homem que tem todos os seus inimigos destruidos que mais resta para fazer? Voltar ao antecedente Altair = EU", "hours": 21.2, "username": "Gaicoz o Vil\u00e3o \u1566(\u00f2_\u00f3\u02c7)\u1564", "products": 471, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 185, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "This was yet another fantastic Assassin's Creed game. The game series just keeps getting better with every new release. If you enjoy very large and immersive environments, and medieval type combat with an emphasis on stealth without any limitations, you should definitely consider this game along with its previous releases. If you enjoy the genre, this game should be an easy choice. I'd give it a 9.5 out of 10.", "hours": 28.2, "username": "SirDeity", "products": 299, "early_access": false}
