{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "I love the Assassin's Creed series so much! Fluid free running makes this game. Can't wait for 3!", "hours": 37.8, "username": "Coodoo", "products": 634, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Another incremental refinement on the Assassin's Creed formula. The dispatch quests and clan recruitment features return from AC: Brotherhood, and now there's ne \"Tower Defense\" style Hideout Defense segments, for better or worse.\nMultiplayer is similarly expanded on, with more and better gamemodes, new maps and custimazation options, and better post-match voting and party continuation options. Unfortunately, the multiplayer still follows a Call of Duty style leveling and perks system, and the EXP curve can be frustratingly low - meaning you're not going to get to use the toys you see everyone else with until you've put a decent amount of time into the game.\nBasically, it's another yealry AC release, and it manages to add just enough to the experience to stave off boredom for maybe one more year. Just in time to leave behind Ezio's story for AC III.", "hours": 9.7, "username": "Soul Unison", "products": 336, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Interesting singleplayer if you're into the story of Altair and Etzio but the MP is where the game shines. The game is already a bit low on players but it's still not difficult to find a game.", "hours": 60.7, "username": "CptTrips", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "ACR picks off right after the events of Brotherhood. While the gameplay and mechanics are the same, Ubisoft have brought in several new things to this title. You can now recruit dozens of Assassin's and place them in cities (a strategy type mini-game whereby you can control cities and ensure they do not fall under templar control), access to bombs and new city-defence mini-games. All in all, the storyline is as smart as ever as you play as Ezio but this time it takes place in Istanbul, Turkey. The music needs no introduction: it's ace! While you may feel that this feels like ACB, the Multiplayer is as fun as ever and overall I had an amazing time attempting to unlock and complete the whole Singleplayer campaign with 100%; which I later managed after many many hours.\nA must buy. 8/10!", "hours": 68.8, "username": "Merchant2006 - Streaming Live!", "products": 477, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Other than the added tower defense game play, I liked Revelations quite a bit.  Old Ezio is best Ezio.", "hours": 19.0, "username": "FatBaby[Kin]", "products": 490, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Is this game as good as the rest of the series? No. But it tries. ACR is only guilty of testing out too many new mechanics, most of which fall flat. But fans of the series will come to realize the game still has charm, if you play the way it's meant to be played.", "hours": 67.1, "username": "[WANG]Raggafragga", "products": 266, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-09", "text": "Despite enjoying the franchise up to now (especially 2 and Brotherhood), I came into AC:R with low expectations due to a lot the media claiming it was probably the worst in the series so far. That might actually be true, but this is still a good Assassin's Creed game that should satisfy fans of the series. Just don't go into it thinking it's going to be the high mark of the series, because it's not. It also doesn't really live up to its name, as the story is still every bit as convoluted as it was before this entry.\nThat said, if you've enjoyed all the AC offerings up to this point, you'll likely enjoy this one as well.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "ExoHazMatt", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-08", "text": "Stab people in the back. The front works too. There is a lot of focus on stabbing people. It's an odd concept to build a game world around.", "hours": 9.4, "username": "Glistening Fish Lifters", "products": 197, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 187, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-07", "text": "The last chapter in the \"Ezio Trilogy,\" Assassin's Creed: Revelations (AC:R) concludes the stories of Alta\u00efr ibn La-Ahad and Ezio Auditore da Firenze creatively binding the two together providing a satisfying ending. AC:R streamlines the action and breaks up the tediousness of climbing by combining elements from the past games and by introducing the \"hookblade.\" The game also features \"Desmond Sequences\" that are a unique form of first-person platforming missions, but are served as unlockable levels. It should be noted that three downloadable content packs are available: Ancestors Character Pack, Mediterranean Traveler Map Pack and The Lost Archive. The Lost Archive is a singleplayer expansion to the rather monotonous \"Desmond Sequences.\"", "hours": 21.7, "username": "Hairbautt", "products": 674, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-18", "text": "This game is awesome, and a must have if your a fan of the series. This game features more tatics and assassnation moves than ever. Lots of new places to see, new cities and a great story. This game is the last game with Ezio Auditore the main character in the series, but also features Altiare the assassin in the first game. This game get's a 10 out of 10 as far as im concerned and is a must play.", "hours": 9.9, "user_id": "76561198030715975", "username": "Ranger", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-12", "text": "idk really i like the muliplayer its fun to kill people and get rewarded......", "hours": 34.0, "username": "SniperKnighter", "products": 166, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-10", "text": "The weakest of all AC titles, almost no revelations at all.\nIt only concludes the story of Ezio/Altair which was epic, but the game is very short, the tower defense missions are horrible, you have to go back once in a while to defend towers from being attacked over and over again..\nThe gameplay remains the same like the previous installments, which is good, the music is excellent as always and the story is the best thing in this game, but this sequel won't tell you much..\nThe MP is quite fun and original, but very frustrating sometimes.\nMy Rating: 8/10", "hours": 64.4, "username": "\u2b50ChapaNDJ\u2b50", "products": 1380, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-09", "text": "Like with most Assassin's Creed games, you play them for the story, not innovations in the gameplay over preview games. You should only get this game if you are interested in the story. It may be a bit of a filler but it definitely pumps you up for the next game in the series. Worth a sale purchase for the fans of the series.\n----[Rating weighted based on the genre]----\nI'm basing my rating on the game being part of a larger whole of the series. I do not recommend playing this game on it's own.\nStory: 5/5\nGameplay: 4/5\nChallenge: 2.5/5\nDiscovery: 3/5\nReplayability: 3/5\nAesthetics: 3.5/5\nVisuals: 5/5\nAtmosphere: 2.5/5\nMusic: 4/5", "hours": 23.1, "username": "Demian", "products": 229, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-07", "text": "Not as good as Brotherhood, they tried adding more features and ended up making it worse. However it does give a good send off for Ezio and is well worth a play for anyone who is a fan of the Assassins Creed franchise.", "hours": 54.9, "user_id": "76561198016742689", "username": "Potatoesss", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-29", "text": "Ezio is getting old, but is showing no signs of weakness. The final chapter in the ACII spin-offs goes out with... not that great of a bang. To say this game is worth 50 dollars is a longshot, but fans of the series will have long time questions answered. However, they will soon be replaced by more questions. All in all, if you're a fan of Assassin's Creed, you will find some repitition in this one, but at the same time, there is enough good to make you want to keep playing.", "hours": 19.1, "username": "Low Res Guy", "products": 240, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-23", "text": "\u041e\u0433\u043e\u043d\u044c \u0440\u0435\u0431\u044f\u0442\u0430!!! \u0421\u0438\u043d\u0433\u043b \u0441\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440. \u041c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043a \u0442\u043e\u0436\u0435. 10/10", "hours": 14.8, "username": "zveroncheg", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-18", "text": "this game is totally awesome, but not to the level of older versions, about MP, they totally ruined  it  and they wont fix it as they were busy with DLCs and money milking, dont buy it for MP as you will get  disappointed and bored. but for SP, no matter how many times i play this, ACB or AC2,i never get disappointed and its very enjoyable experience.", "hours": 49.7, "username": "Abook", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-16", "text": "Short version: worth it. That is all.", "hours": 104.4, "username": "Sovereign [CHL]", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 188, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-14", "text": "Great game! It's not as good as the Assassin's Creed 2 or Brotherhood, but a must play for fans of the series!", "hours": 15.5, "username": "Connex", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-05-08", "text": "YAAAAAAAAAAAWN.  It's AC1 all over again.   Stick with Brotherhood, skip Revelations.\n4/10.", "hours": 16.3, "user_id": "76561197992841476", "username": "Dactylartha", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-07", "text": "I've only just started to play Revelations, I must say it has been good for the most part. There are a few things that urk me though, for one the character models for Desmond, Ezio and Altair (Clay somewhat included). I loved the way the characters looked in Brotherhood, but now Desmond looks like Adam Sandler, Ezio's head is more of a Gorilla shape/void of emotion, and the first thing I noticed about Altair is that his nose is bigger than his whole face. Speaking of Altair, the voice actor they used to replace him; while I understand the change of accent seeing how he is in that type of area, I don't like the fact that Altair's voice is deeper. Another thing that sort of bothers me is the aspect that your Templar meter goes up everytime you renovate a location, I understand why they put this in considering you're building up in an area where they would be looking for brotherhood activity, but they could have at least implimented more than just bribing Heralds and killing witness.", "hours": 29.4, "username": "Aracnel", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-05", "text": "What a way to\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665all over a perfect series. One of the developers said \"there isn't much we can do with Ezio at this point.\" Except make another game and charge a high class hooker's blow job price. That's the laziness of these developers, All they had to do was stitch this game together with Brotherhood and boo yah...You got two games in one, loads of DLC along with Ezio dying off perfectly in his little \"Pixar \" movie...Not only would they have made money, they would have made money with a more reasonable game. No justification calls for glitches and  bugs in this one, and this game was alot more interesting than Brotherhood. Altair again got thrown under the bus, 6 missions with him and he's dead to you. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 off Ubisoft.", "hours": 431.6, "username": "Bandit|MerC|", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-02", "text": "Simplesmente Fant\u00e1stico! \u00d3timos Gr\u00e1ficos, jogabilidade, e hist\u00f3ria. Multiplayer muito bom tbm. Uma saga \u00e9pica!", "hours": 53.5, "username": "Murdock", "products": 259, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-01", "text": "This is what I was expecting when I played Brotherhood. A call back to the first game, a decent look at the theme of aging with relation to the protagonist, and a sense of progress for the series. Unfortunately since Brotherhood was lacking these important qualities but brought everything else to the table, Revelations comes across as a retread which is a shame.\nThankfully, this game puts the story of Ezio and Altair to a satisfying conclusion and even manages to develop the character of Desmond Miles somewhat. At the very least, the game has set itself up for a solid arc in the third game.\nMultiplayer here is...hard to discuss. On one hand, significant improvements have been made to the mechanics of how abilities and movement works in this game but  the game glitches a worrying amount of time. Additionally, the contract system is poorly designed, for example: I once recieved the 1st place player (I was his only pursuer) but I recieved three pursuers while I was ranked 4th or 6th.", "hours": 235.3, "user_id": "76561198014429410", "username": "Sepgreti", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-25", "text": "You must try this game! Its Awsome!", "hours": 5.9, "username": "FodeX", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-24", "text": "As a fan of the series it pains me to say I was not very impressed with Revelations. The game was not bad, but it did absolutely nothing new compared to Brotherhood. I have no MP experience, so maybe that's where it improved. Otherwise this is just Brotherhood with some stuff tacked on. The upgrades to the Assasin's in general were cool, but overwhelmingly tedious/confusing. All the cities, all the dens. Yuck. The bombs were straight up OP so I declined to use them - at all. The city was massive, and while parts were great, most of it was just brown drivel. I did not feel like there was much incentive to explore like in previous games. Combat was\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665easy - although I'll excuse this as Ezio by this time was the master of all combat forms.... The economy seemed even more tedious than before. Dungeons were too easy - although very unique and entertaining. Characters all muddled together - either that or I'm a racist. And for a game called \"Revelations\" the ending didn't answer much.", "hours": 27.7, "username": "Skud", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-22", "text": "\u0418\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441))))))", "hours": 31.8, "username": "GreeN", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-22", "text": "The faster pacing, tighter story, more fun and just plain cool gameplay combined with shorter lulls between the sexy stabby stabby action, Revelations is the best Assassin's Creed game to date.", "hours": 31.3, "username": "Fieryspirit", "products": 592, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 189, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-14", "text": "Reveals very little, despite the title... Recycled gameplay is still fun after all these years. Main characters remain intriguing, though the tale of the main protagonist is not concluded in any satisfactory way. Istanbul is a fun place to visit. Very much on the short side for this series and only worth getting on discount.", "hours": 37.4, "user_id": "76561198031538705", "username": "johntheobscure", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-13", "text": "Even more beautiful than AC2 and ACB, with more new interesting characters and polished multiplayer. Beware though: you most likely won't be able to play with your friends due to NAT restrictions.", "hours": 26.9, "username": "Von the Wat?", "products": 1177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-11", "text": "I used to hate assassins creed because i had only player the first one.\nNow I LOVE IT!", "hours": 25.2, "username": "Metroidsax1", "products": 214, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-04-09", "text": "Awesome multiplayer... IF you buy it for Xbox, I would NOT recomend buying this for PC, I spent 6 hours trying to get my NAT open so I could actualy connect to more then 1 in a million multiplayer sessions but to no avail, went out and bought it for xbox, bam open NAT, hours of fun :P", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Renmaru", "products": 480, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-08", "text": "The final chapter of Ezio Auditore, and what a truly amazing journey he has had.  This installment, although called 'Revelations', opens up knew doors in the magnificant story of the assassins and the templers.  Completely meddling with your already muddled mind.  With all the favorourite assassin abilities, such as air assassinations, free running, throwing knifes and the hidden blade; Revelations continues with Brotherhood ability to call on other assassins when you are in need and adds the abiity to use ziplines with your new 'Hook' blade.  The game does get a little bit repetative towards the end, but if you love the series you will love this installment.  8.5/10 Ubisoft,  Bring on Creed 3.  (And start explaining everthing).", "hours": 30.3, "username": "Ritchie", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-03", "text": "A game worth getting. This game has got to be one of the BEST games I've ever played. The graphics are amazing. The gameplay is creative. And the different things you can do is limitless. The multiplayer is fun and a great time spender. This game is worth it.", "hours": 109.5, "username": "\u3010=\u25c8\ufe3f\u25c8=\u3011", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-03", "text": "You know that feel you get when you really wanted soemthing only for it to be one of the worst things ever. Thats what buying this felt like. ALTHOUGH THE BOMBS ARE PRETTY SWEET. Protip: If the game crashes its becuase it hates it when you longjump, I almost wish I was making that up.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "Terro", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-03", "text": "IMO, its the best one yet. I remember IGN saying that they did a great job of blending 3 generations of Assassins into one fluid story...and they couldn't be more right. It was seamlessly and brilliantly done. I really don't think I've been as intrigued since Bioshock. And that's saying a lot, haha. So yeah, would definitely recommend it.", "hours": 4.1, "username": "AggressiveAtlas", "products": 273, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-31", "text": "ACR is the latest installment to the AC series. The story continues with Desmond and Ezio. If you followed the AC series then this will be an excellent addition to your list. The physics and overall gameplay has been improved, but as usual sometimes they just don't do what you want. Hopefully with improvements in the games this will be better in future. Overall the story remains as excellent and puts more light on what happened. Additional videos and content are only available on the other side of the world though.\nThe one problem that most followers of the series will have is that the version available in the US is much more limited than the ones available in Australia for example. Additional maps and characters, items and side-stories that are not available and are region locked made many shy away from this. Personally I only purchased it because I got a coupon for 50% off - else I would not have purchased it for the original price without the perks that are available elsewhere.", "hours": 73.3, "username": "Useless (\u6b7b)", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-30", "text": "very addicting multiplayer and singler player is always good", "hours": 18.9, "user_id": "76561198009092427", "username": "Lord Sasuke", "products": 255, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 190, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-29", "text": "Excelente jogo! estou com a cole\u00e7\u00e3o completa! aguardando assassin's creed 3 ansiosamente!!!!", "hours": 9.2, "username": "luizuramg", "products": 522, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-03-27", "text": "Seems really dumbed down; relying more heavily on (their not so good) combat instead of any intriguing puzzles. Tells you when to use eagle vision too often. I'm only amused by the free roaming and the plot, but find myself missing the puzzles and other rich elements that were in 2 and 3. I would NOT recomend paying the full price of this game.\nedit* Why did this get changed to recommended??", "hours": 27.5, "username": "Pidge", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-24", "text": "Man the games just get better and better! :D More kill animations, better Assassin recruits and missions, more\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665to do and now there are bombs~! Multiplayer is much better now and it has a small storyline to it. CAN'T WAIT FOR AC3!! AKFH kalhfkl ahklf ahklf jakljfl jag;klf h", "hours": 51.4, "username": "bashscrazy", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-21", "text": "A good conclusion to the Ezio story arc of Assassin's Creed. As refined as Brotherhood but lacking in content. Not as many side quests to do. The general story line is shorter than that of the previous 2. Having said that, it still does give you a good insight into Altair as well as Ezio. And good to see he finally hooks up with a chick, after having missed so many opportunities in the other games :p\nStill a good game and especially worth it if you've played the previous two and want to see it to the end. If you haven't played the previous two then highly recommend playing them first.", "hours": 25.2, "username": "bombs", "products": 326, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-21", "text": "\uc644\ubcbd \ud55c\uae00\ud654, \ub2e4\uc591\ud55c \ubbf8\uc158\ub4e4, \uba4b\uc9c4 \uc5f0\ucd9c... \uc808\ub300 \ud6c4\ud68c \uc548\ud558\uc2e4\uac81\ub2c8\ub2e4.", "hours": 11.5, "user_id": "76561198053710341", "username": "Vancomycin", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-18", "text": "For me, this is a #2 game in series after the original\n. Take the best parts from previous releases, combine it with something brand new - and here you got\n. I loved the storyline and multiplayer as well (though a mess with titles & emblems is unnecessary). Special thanks for the \"Desmond's Journey\".", "hours": 102.6, "username": "(GoR)Andrew.zhd", "products": 353, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-18", "text": "2 assassins, one destiny. Another entry in Assassisns Creed series with good innovations and storytelling. Revelations shows us final moments of Ezio Auditore as he travels to Constantinople where he must find keys to sacred chamber in Masyaf where assassisins were born. While gameplay stays same like past 2 games only new thing we get is bomb crafting. You can find various elements to craft different bombs for different situations. Buy new armor upgrades, different weapons,, upgrading shops, training your assassins and sending them to other cities all same from past game but better. As you progress you also can play as Altair to see what happens before and after events of first game. Multiplayer is great in its own way, different missions to play very fun to enjoy with friends. Overall best game of series, but short.", "hours": 12.6, "user_id": "76561197972913813", "username": "Bladewolf", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-17", "text": "Another 10/10 game in the series. One thing that gets overlooked is the music in the AC series, its really done well.  Ezio's story is wrapped up perfectly, as is Altair's. Memorable characters, great story, fun gameplay, tight controls, amazing music. Just a 10/10.", "hours": 58.9, "username": "418", "products": 321, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-16", "text": "\u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430", "hours": 25.7, "username": "Dart Vader", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-16", "text": "Assassin's Creed games are great in general, but they should've called this one AC 2.75 or something. It's basically ACII AND Brotherhood all over again, but this time there's practically nothing new. Yes, there are bombs (which I hardly used), a hookblade (which was actually pretty good), a parachute (never used it; only for the story) and a tower defense mini-game (which works alright, but doesn't belong in the game if you ask me), but it's just not enough to call this a NEW Assassin's Creed game. They're really milking the franchise.\nHowever, the story IS told in a better way and you get to play as both Altair and Ezio. You also get to play as Desmond, obviously, but that's only a matter of minutes, thankfully. Desmond's segments are critical to the story, but it diminishes the gameplay experience. It just pulls you out of the entire experience.\nAll in all, you really can't go wrong with AC. Just don't expect too much from it.\n[Rating: 77/100]", "hours": 10.7, "username": "mark | dj.", "products": 3577, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 191, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-15", "text": "One of the most epic stories I have ever experienced.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "talon", "products": 334, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-14", "text": "ITS AWSOME!!!!!! you collect data fragments for desmonds chiled hood. Ezio goes to were Altiar was in the creed 3 games ago lol. And you still recruit assassin's for all of you who liked that in brotherhood. and Ezio gets a little surgar whith a atalian girl named Sofia. No NO SEX for the assassins creed fan's.More places for you assassin's to go and you can even take over cities of templar control. you can craft bombs, new assassi'n kill moves,and its just really fun.SO....BUY IT PLAY IT LOVE IT!", "hours": 227.5, "user_id": "76561198031280502", "username": "[C3:M] Bubbanator", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-03-12", "text": "The finisher to Ezio's era of Assassin's Creed, Revealations is a step backwards from previous games. It is clear that the developers are out of ideas and have no idea how to progress the series foward after switching to the CoD style yearly release.\nWhereas in the previous games, Brotherhood, factions such as the mercenaries or thieves would have multiple side quest missions with their own rewards, Revelations only has 1 mission for the mercenaries and the Romani.\nThe story itself lacks any clear enemy in your search for 5 keys that contains a diary from Altair, and the main quest line (really, the only quest line) can be completed within 20 hours. There are insights to what happens to Altair after the first game but it's better to save your money and look up spoilers of the game than to play through this snoozer.", "hours": 46.8, "username": "Mikeon", "products": 490, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed Part 4: Assassin's Creed 2 part 3 (or AC2 part 2 part 2)", "hours": 17.0, "username": "Dire Miralis", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-09", "text": "This Assassins Creed was amazing! I totally loved Revelations and how it brought you back and forth from the past and present in the game. It was a really in-depth game. The world to explore is massive and there is so much detail in everything. The costumes of the characters were magnificent in color and style. The gameplay was fluid and extremely hard to put down. There is alot of extra stuff to complete which makes the game alot more fun then just playing the game straight through. If you do play the game straight through you will be surprised on how short it can be. There are only 9 sequences to complete. I would suggest playing the previous Creeds in this series before playing this one. The fighting is awesome and you can combine moves and kills with each swing of the sword. The online aspect is dead. The minor bugs in the game are quickly overlooked due to the great story and style this game has. I highly recommend this game to anyone who is a fan of series.", "hours": 25.4, "username": "NorkDorf On Twitch {Live}", "products": 8235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-09", "text": "Clearly it's not the best of the series (I'd give that to Assassin's Creed II) and this game feels alot more like a filler or an extra part of the whole Ezio saga. However it does conclude Ezio's (finally) AND Altair's story.", "hours": 19.2, "username": "Annie T. Mood", "products": 1091, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-08", "text": "Very good", "hours": 61.4, "username": "lucasmachadom4", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-07", "text": "Great game. And also a great, interweaving conclusion to Ezio's and Alta\u00efr's stories.", "hours": 41.1, "username": "Frawns", "products": 234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-06", "text": "It's multiplayer mode is better than brotherhood,maybe story is a bit short but learning Altair's history and seeing how Ezio's quest finished is really exciting.You should definitely buy it !", "hours": 43.3, "username": "Tulpar1988", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-06", "text": "+1", "hours": 28.7, "user_id": "76561197960448494", "username": "Paradox", "products": 269, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 192, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-05", "text": "9.8/10 Amazing Sequel, Ezio's story wraps up perfectly, and you even get closure on Altair which was a fantastic touch. The combination of stories flow perfectly together. Ezio is a legend and truly is the most interesting man in the world. AC2 /ACBH/ and ACRev will always be in my top stories of all time.", "hours": 27.4, "username": "Demadizzle", "products": 473, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 193, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-04", "text": "\u0441\u044e\u0436\u0435\u0442\u043d\u0443\u044e \u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0442\u0430\u043a \u0438 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0448\u0435\u043b (\u043d\u0430\u0434\u043e\u0435\u043b\u043e) , \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f))\n\u0430 \u043c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0435\u0440 \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0443\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0438 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 ))\nP.s. \u0445\u043e\u0442\u044f \u0432 \u0441\u0442\u0438\u043c\u0435 \u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430 ((", "hours": 6.8, "username": "protiv vseh", "products": 198, "early_access": false}
