{"product_id": "201870", "page": 193, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-28", "text": "\u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bc\u03ac\u03c4\u03b1 \u03b1\u03b3\u03cd\u03c1\u03c4\u03b7! Ezio in Constantinople. Enough said.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "Borracho", "products": 794, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 193, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-02-27", "text": "Really? Same\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665different city!\nAnd how old is Ezio now I'm surprised he could even make it up a one story building without a zimmerframe..\nThis is just getting stupid now, it's time to move on. They have tried to make the game more fresh with different mechanics but it doesn't work. This game is just an excuse to tie up loose ends in a story people are becomming disintrested with.\nI only bought it for the story, Game play is ok, and this is CLEARLY a console port.\nAnd WTH is with Desmonds little \"Tetris\" adventure.\nAnd as for the Multiplayer I quote: \"'I've got nothing against multiplayer as a concept, but you shouldn't try to make it carry a game because there are logistical problems.\"", "hours": 15.1, "username": "Tularis", "products": 480, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 193, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-23", "text": "Yes, it is another yearly iteration of the series, but no, its not terrible, in fact i think its better structured than brotherhood was in quite a few areas. the story was good this time, made sense, and i finally understood ezio's motivations a bit more.\ncomplaints.\n1, this could have been longer i cant help but feel that the story was really short...and in this series that's really all that matters to me. it was good, but in comparison to 2, it was short.\n2, the soundtrack was less memorable than 2.\n3, the bombs are great, could have used them in earlier games, but you can get by in the game without ever really using them. one way i think they could improve on this is some sort of xp system tied to certain skills, where you get better at things by doing them. and having more utility uses for bombs, like revealing hidden areas in the platforming sections, or knocking over objects to create a path.\nhave not touched the multiplayer yet, but i think its self explanatory.", "hours": 16.0, "username": "Sir Hallin", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-21", "text": "You play as a loveable italian pizza boy who's family was murdered and the love of his life, Laqwanda Laticia Laranda O'neal (voiced by christopher walken) was kidnapped by a greasy mexican, El Diablo (also voiced by Christopher Walken) who runs a string of taco joints around the world. In a quest for vengeance, this pizza boy must thwart El Diablo in his plans for world domination by delivering pizza's at light speed and putting El Diablo out of business.\nAre you man enough?", "hours": 68.2, "username": "Millor", "products": 373, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-20", "text": "The story and landscape are stunning. Just love all AC series.", "hours": 65.7, "username": "Ace [MY]", "products": 288, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-11", "text": "If you played AC and wondered what happened to Altiar then this is the best follow up game, as it explains events after taking back Masyaf.\nACR in itself is just a continuation of Ezio's story, while not concluded (imo). Its the usual run around/climb buildings we loved in AC1.", "hours": 18.4, "user_id": "76561198025531453", "username": "NoobGamer", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-28", "text": "If your a fan of AC then get the game you know you have to. The story is good the attacks are good etc, I havent tried multiplayer yet so dont know how that will be but to me that is only a bonus i only by AC for the story.", "hours": 15.4, "username": "Knifering", "products": 625, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-27", "text": "As per usual, this game picks up where the last one left off and delivers twice as hard. It can safely be said by now (at least with this series) that everything that was good about the previous game is expanded and improved upon in the latest installment. Moreover, this game provides a challenging and rewarding multiplayer experience rivaled by few games.", "hours": 230.7, "user_id": "76561197998961798", "username": "[XI] 1.21 GIGAWATTS?!??", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-24", "text": "Uh-mazing. Play it now!", "hours": 37.1, "username": "The Dragon", "products": 295, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-21", "text": "I've always dreamed of being an Assassin whose charms rivals that of Casanova and that  comes true in Assassin's Creed Revelations.  I still have that Disability of jumping off roofs like a someone committing suicide, when it should be a swan dive into a cart full of hay but that's not the games fault...I think!", "hours": 41.3, "user_id": "76561198025324287", "username": "Missy_Moo", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-16", "text": "The single-player's a bit inessential after the plot progression from Brotherhood, but it's still great fun, and the improved multiplayer is really awesome. Unfortunately suffers from a few crashes and glitches, but I can't speak for everyone's experience.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "Scribbly", "products": 742, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-15", "text": "This games multiplayer is so much fun, and its so different than any other game, takes skill, cunning, and deceit.\nBuy this game its a blast!", "hours": 12.1, "username": "\u0110\u025b\u028c\u0189\u0193\u028a\u0194", "products": 849, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 194, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-11", "text": "This game is, like it's precursor's, well made and written. On the other hand it comes to long phrases of running and running and running... and climbing . . . running.\nWell than .... it's Assassin's Creed! What do I expect? =D\nAssassin's Creed - Revelations feels a little bit like Brotherhood, just a bigger City and more exciting quest's and many more peoples.\nFinally it is a good game which improves, that UbiSoft isn't that bad ;-)\nOne drawback because it is not the \"old\" Desmond/Alt\u00e4ir/Ezio model. A new face. Why? Idk.\n9/10", "hours": 17.7, "username": "WasD", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-10", "text": "AWESOME IS AWESOME!", "hours": 40.8, "username": "Kleiver", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-09", "text": "One word - amazing game!", "hours": 42.5, "username": "linas.warrior", "products": 723, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-06", "text": "All the good and bad parts of the rest of the series made it into AC:R. Campy story, glitchy cutscenes, self-indulgent grandeur... it's all here along with the classic stealth and free-running action. Some big plot arcs finally get wrapped up, but for the most part the plot seems to crawl, and the game ends on yet another cliffhanger. The new bomb system is actually well implemented and surprisingly useful, but otherwise combat is pretty much the same. Points deducted for Ubisoft's terrible proprietary Uplay launcher, and the mind-numbingly awful Desmond side-quests.  B-", "hours": 10.0, "username": "chrk", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-05", "text": "This game dissapointed me in a lot of ways, though it impressed me in one.\nGone are the crazy puzzle sections from 'the truth'.  I can't get over that, they were awesome, and added so much 'current time' backstory.\nAs it is, the game has very little connection to the current time, the primary plot thread  literally does not move until the end of the game.\nSomething cool they did add though is the portal-like puzzle sections for desmond's backstory.  Though interesting, his backstory is too much of a retread.\nAnyway it was worth what I paid for it, but I can't really reccoemend it unless it's $30 or less.", "hours": 31.2, "username": "Sardonic", "products": 718, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-04", "text": "For three consecutive years, Ubisoft has been releasing new installments to its Assassin's Creed franchise. My fears with such quick sequels were quelled with Brotherhood, which bested its already remarkable predecessor by a mile. Needless to say, Revelations had a lot to live up to.\nI'd be hard pressed to highlight memorable additions in this new iteration. While Revelations recaptures what made its prequels amazing, it lacks innovation. The few new inclusions are a tower defense mini-game, bomb crafting, and puzzle sequences featuring Desmond.\nIf you loved Brotherhood's multiplayer, it's still as exhilarating as ever here and the plot remains a meticulous tapestry of fact and fiction. Any fan who has followed the storyline will appreciate this new installment which concludes the journeys of Altair and Ezio in heartwarming fashion.\nAt the end of the day, Revelations is still worth recommending, despite it coming off as more of an expansion than a full-fledged sequel.\nGrade: B+", "hours": 38.5, "username": "DaNCeSWiTHBuLLeTS", "products": 1967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-03", "text": "Heya, Almog here friend of the real Rander and real owner of AC:R.\nI recommend this game to everyone who enjoys an open world with a few factions and their little challenges, just beating down guards, following an epic journey after a failed too-old-too-ambitious for his own good Ezio Auditore Da Firenze.\nThe game itself quite disappointed me after all the babling about playing with both Ezio and Altair when you can only play Altair and some stages.\nThe game's engine itself got improved more and more, the only two bad things is (one mentioned above) and the other is the horrible interface, I have to wear my glasses to see how much templar awareness I have?\nAnyway I was very very satisfied with the multiplayer, playing as (spoiler) Vali the rogue assassin and other semi-assassin-mission targets is an awesome idea.\nI would not recommend the DLC too much but its a fun idea if you wish to be more hidden then usual, especially at rome and port maps.\nRating: 7.8, GET IT, LOVE IT!", "hours": 75.2, "username": "Peasant Lord of Winter", "products": 477, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 195, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-02", "text": "The online multiplayer alone is worth the asking price for this game. I skipped over Brotherhood, so the multiplayer system was new to me -- I've been incredibly impressed. Definitely recommended.", "hours": 32.6, "username": "Cornslop", "products": 421, "early_access": false}
