{"product_id": "201870", "page": 197, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "\u041e\u0434\u0438\u043d \u0438\u0437 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u043c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u044d\u0432\u0435\u0440.", "hours": 93.4, "username": "UnclDeD", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 197, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Really enjoying Assassin's Creed Revelations. Just as much as Brotherhood. If you enjoyed Brotherhood, you'll enjoy this one too!", "hours": 56.8, "user_id": "76561198007793428", "username": "BlackSabre", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Decent game.  Has a new base defense minigame that's pretty interesting.  The multiplayer isn't as good as Brotherhood, IMO, and the storyline feels weaker than its predecessor but it's decent enough all in all.", "hours": 45.8, "username": "Yorke Hunt", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Look, if you're buying or thinking of buying Assassin's Creed: Revelations, you probably loved AC2, and maybe even Brotherhood. Revelations is not those games. The single-player is like a cramped, rather poorly planed Venice, that you need a loading screen to see the other half of. The story isn't great, though some of the characters are. But if you liked AC:B's multiplayer, this is a must-have. Improvements and refinements, new maps (that all seem the same for the first few hours, and kind of are) and just a better experience in general. THEY TOOK THE \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ING DOCTOR AWAY.", "hours": 38.4, "username": "Orv", "products": 1134, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Not a console port.", "hours": 4.9, "username": "Knudsen", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "I've written many recommendations for the entire Assassin's Creed franchise. Yet here I find myself at a loss for words. This is the one of those series, that just keeps getting better and better. I think I can count the amount of series that can boast that, on one hand. Revelations takes the amazing parts of Assassin's Creed and adds a pinch of reality. You don't just run around aimlessly butchering stuff, you need to take up the mantle of being the Mentor for the entire brotherhood, you need to direct attacks, organize defense on a much larger scale than you used to, all while attempting to progress the story and learning your part in the grand scheme of things.", "hours": 46.0, "username": "Apathy", "products": 595, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "An excellent finale to a great tale of both Ezio Audiotre da Firenze and Altair. Must play if you're an AC fan.", "hours": 47.3, "username": "Neon", "products": 762, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "assassin's creed <3", "hours": 23.6, "username": "DragNviper13", "products": 533, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Its fun! Play it!", "hours": 34.9, "username": "Nucking Futz", "products": 826, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "This was the best assassins creed of the series i believe. Really enjoyed the story!", "hours": 17.7, "user_id": "76561197986715048", "username": "gottablaze \u272a", "products": 135, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "tres bon jeux\ndecor extraordinaire et varier\ndes mision de tou sorte recruter des assasin apeler les pour vous aidez\nmultijoeur exelent sof nivo de lvl des joueur ou ce nai pa equilibre detre lvl 1 et tomber sur des 50", "hours": 27.3, "user_id": "76561198006880866", "username": "corvo <[o_0]>", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 198, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "A fitting end to the Assassin's Creed II storyline that nicely wraps up many questions, fills in much needed details, and leaves you wondering where things will go next.  The Den Defense mini-games, a tower-defense style mini-game, are an interesting addition to the various activities you'll find around the city.  I did miss the larger environments and the horses, but honestly, they didn't add much to the game.  The Assassin's Apprentice missions really add more character to the Brotherhood concept that the last game brought to the table, and really serve to make you form a bit of a bond with each of the assassins you recruit, rather than just more fodder for you to throw at guards.  The first-person Desmond missions were boring and repetitive and barely provided any story for the amount of time spent just to unlock them, then by plodding through the yawn-inducing puzzles.  I'd rather they'd expanded on or done something similar to the previous game's modern-day Monteriggioni sequence", "hours": 35.7, "username": "MX OneFive", "products": 986, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 199, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Another great entry in the Assassin's Creed series, Revelations begins right where Brotherhood left off and has you controlling an aging Ezio Auditore through 16th century Constantinople and exploring memories throughout the life of Altair. The story is mostly focused around wrapping up the tales of Ezio and Altair's lives but Desmond's story continues to move forward as well, and as usual there is a cliffhanger ending that leaves you in heavy anticipation for the next game.", "hours": 43.2, "username": "JNS| TwoSheds", "products": 833, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 199, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "EZIO AND ALTAIR DIE", "hours": 9.4, "username": "REG", "products": 390, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 199, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "It's surely a massive joy to live \u0130stanbul andto breathe through Ezio and Altair. The ones who played the games before must play this as well.", "hours": 50.3, "username": "Rind", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
