{"product_id": "201870", "page": 199, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-24", "text": "AC:R does everything that AC2 and AC:B did right, and adds to it. There is just as much faffing about as you like though it's mostly not required. Horses are inexplicably missing, but you get to recruit much earlier. The tower defence segment can suck a fat one. Also, the begger women are back in packs. The setting and cutscenes are beautiful, as is the smooth combat. I give it 9.9 ! and highly recommend to all.", "hours": 37.0, "username": "AzzKikr143", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 199, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-19", "text": "Best game of 2011 & most likely 2012.", "hours": 53.9, "user_id": "76561198005732984", "username": "Clockworks", "products": 322, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 199, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-19", "text": "Certainly an enjoyable game for fans of the series. It seems that the devs have taken to heart the things that bogged the previous games down a little and changed/removed them.\nBombs are just a touch overpowered, but they do certainly help to fill a void in gameplay - although it feels like Ezio is turning into Batman with all his gadgets now.\nBut yeah... good game, check it out.", "hours": 9.6, "username": "Sadface", "products": 677, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 200, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-19", "text": "Best game of 2011 & most likely 2012.", "hours": 53.9, "user_id": "76561198005732984", "username": "Clockworks", "products": 322, "early_access": false}
