{"product_id": "201870", "page": 200, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-11", "text": "\u0414\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0439\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0438 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0435\u0446 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0434\u0432\u0443\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0433\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0435\u0432! 9/10", "hours": 64.1, "username": "Blast", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 200, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-10", "text": "The fact that as many as 7 Ubisoft Studios have been working on this game, makes the fact that this is the worst game in the series even harder to bear.\nThe story is great, but the game has been dumped down in every other way. The Virtual Trainings has been replaced by short tutorials on how to throw a knife or a bomb... The horses are completely non-existent, except for some horses pulling carriages in specific interactive cutscenes. The right hand hidden blade has been replaced by a so called \"Hook Blade\" that replaces the Leap Jump. Basically, the Hook Blade works like Leap Jump, but allows you to reach longer. However, you can only do it where the Hook Blade is able to reach, and no longer whereever you want. This removes the ability to jump straight up, and then reach your arms to a side to grab a ledge.\nThey've added a new type of enemy that cannot be killed, except with counters. And they attack once in ten years, so you become extremely frustrated fast.\nContinued in comments", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Morten", "products": 276, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 201, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-10", "text": "Is a good game I recomed!!!!!!!!!!!!!!", "hours": 39.7, "username": "Firefox", "products": 120, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 201, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-09", "text": "Wow, where to begin..... Uh, this game completely owns all of the other Assassin Creed games, it's amazing, better graphics, new really cool fighting moves, it's just amazing", "hours": 20.0, "username": "Decrepified", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 201, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-09", "text": "A lot of jokes about Ezio's old\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665here... Love it!", "hours": 42.4, "username": "C\u00f6nstans\"lemmy\"Barr\u00f6n", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 201, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-08", "text": "This game was excellent, you get to play old ezio, young/old altair and of course desmond and i really felt like i have learnt alot from the characters and the story they are trying to tell. The gameplay is the same but  with a few new features like the tower defence type game on your assasins dens and being able to use bombs and ziplines etc. I did miss the wealth of locations in the previous games but still it was alot of fun being in a different location with different types of people and enemies. Again definitely recommend it if you enjoy any of the games but i'd recommend you play them in order to follow whats going on.", "hours": 18.3, "username": "Invisible Man", "products": 514, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 201, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-08", "text": "\u0425\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0448\u0435\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0445\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0448\u0435\u0439 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b.\n\u0414\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0430\u044f , \u043a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430\u044f , \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u044b\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0430\u044f \u043e \u043f\u043e\u0445\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0445 \u042d\u0446\u0438\u043e  \u0438 \u0410\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0438\u0440\u0430 (\u0412\u0441\u0435 \u0447\u0442\u043e \u0431\u044b\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0434\u0440\u043e\u043c \u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e).\n\u041c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0435\u0440 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043d . \u041e\u043d \u043e\u0442\u0448\u043b\u0438\u0444\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0434\u043e \u0431\u043b\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043e \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u044b\u0434\u0443\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c\u044e. \u0412 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043c \u043c\u0435\u043d\u044f \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442. \u042f \u0434\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d.\n10/10", "hours": 25.1, "username": "YungTekashi", "products": 861, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 201, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-06", "text": "Not really the end of Ezio's life, but his role in the AC series, in my opinion Embers explains his end a lot better. 24hrs to finish the game with everything 100%.\nAssassin's Creed II still better, Revelations is just like Brotherhood.", "hours": 60.8, "username": "ShinjiTomi", "products": 424, "early_access": false}
