{"product_id": "201870", "page": 202, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-04", "text": "Awesome Story , nice ending of the Enzio Triology.\nBut wow the gameplay gets boring, feels like i play Assasins Creed: Brotherhood again with a different story .\nWhen Assasins Creed 3 not brings some new stuff , then is this my last Assasins Creed game ,most disappointed game this year for me , defenatly not worth 50 \u20ac", "hours": 2.9, "username": "DarKshodaN", "products": 2543, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 202, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-04", "text": "if you didnt plan on playing this game, shame on you.", "hours": 92.4, "user_id": "76561198032729592", "username": "Astronomical Cat", "products": 105, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 202, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-03", "text": "Like most AC games lately, it's a further refinement. Unlike just the sprawling content in AssCreed BroHo, it offers a little less total, but what's there is much more detailed. For example, instead of just numbers going up when an protoge becomes a master assassin, you actually have a unique quest set for each master to do! Bombs offer tons of tactical and offensive options. The Hookblade speeds up climbing without being too powerful. Despite all these ideas, I still feel like this game could be better and should not have focused on Ezio again. The very last Da Vinci mission in Brotherhood would have been a much nicer exit to following Ezio.\nAll the same, the game itself is rad. Get it on sale (assuming you have played through the first 3 games!)", "hours": 35.7, "username": "Defenestration", "products": 507, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "201870", "page": 202, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-03", "text": "Revelations' singleplayer portion is the shortest amongst all Assassin's Creed titles, which only took me approximately 4 hours to finish. The game has great voice actors, but the characters are limited by poorly structured cutscenes, and facial animations were often too unnatural to ignore.\nThankfully, Ubisoft has successfully refined the multiplayer portion. New unlocks, character customization options and the return of some Brotherhood maps are very nice additions. In fact, Revelations' multiplayer gameplay is probably the only factor that redeemed this title the privillege of being called an Assassin's Creed game.", "hours": 63.5, "username": "derek328", "products": 44, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
